WEBVTT

00:17.884 --> 00:20.954
CAPTIONING MADE POSSIBLE
BY NEW LINE HOME VIDEO

03:21.100 --> 03:24.070
Agnes:
NURSES CAME FROM ALL OVER
THE UNITED STATES AS WELL,

03:24.070 --> 03:28.074
AND I WAS ONE OF THEM
AND AS EAGER FOR ADVENTURE

03:28.074 --> 03:30.910
AS THE COLLEGE BOYS
WHO VOLUNTEERED.

03:30.910 --> 03:33.079
I DIDN'T KNOW IT
AT THE TIME,

03:33.079 --> 03:36.082
BUT THE CHOICES I MADE IN
NORTHERN ITALY THAT SUMMER

03:36.082 --> 03:38.318
WOULD AFFECT
THE REST OF MY LIFE.

03:39.752 --> 03:41.754
[PARADE MUSIC]

03:41.754 --> 03:43.823
[CHEERING]

04:09.482 --> 04:11.884
[KLAXON HORN HONKING]

04:27.166 --> 04:28.568
MAY I?

04:30.136 --> 04:32.138
THANKS, HARRY.
YOU'RE A GREAT DRIVER.

04:32.138 --> 04:33.740
ANYTIME.

04:35.308 --> 04:36.643
ALLOW ME.

04:36.643 --> 04:38.144
THANKS, HARRY.

04:38.144 --> 04:39.646
WHEW.

04:39.646 --> 04:42.649
I'M SORRY ABOUT
THE BUMPY ROAD THERE,
MISS VON KUROWSKY.

04:42.649 --> 04:45.151
OH, HARRY,
I'M SURE IN TIME

04:45.151 --> 04:47.654
MY DERRIERE WILL LEARN
TO FORGIVE YOU.

04:47.654 --> 04:48.655
POSSO?

04:48.655 --> 04:49.656
OH, SI, GRAZIE.

04:49.656 --> 04:50.657
PREGO.

04:50.657 --> 04:51.724
OH.

04:53.926 --> 04:56.429
DON'T FORGET
ABOUT OUR DATE
FOR ICE CREAM.

04:56.429 --> 04:58.931
WELL, YOU KNOW
WHERE I AM.

04:58.931 --> 05:01.634
WE'RE HERE TO DO A JOB,
REMEMBER?

05:01.634 --> 05:03.703
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

05:05.104 --> 05:07.807
Boy: LA SIGNORA
A UN ANGELO?

05:07.807 --> 05:09.208
BUON GIORNO.

05:11.377 --> 05:13.212
SEI UN ANGELO?

05:14.480 --> 05:19.319
HE THINKS YOU ANGEL
FROM HEAVEN.

05:19.319 --> 05:23.756
WELL, TELL HIM WE'RE JUST
NURSES ARRIVED FROM AMERICA.

05:30.997 --> 05:31.998
MAC?

05:31.998 --> 05:33.333
YEAH?

05:33.333 --> 05:35.835
I HAVE TO FIND
THE BATHROOM.

05:35.835 --> 05:37.837
GRAZIE. GRAZIE.

05:37.837 --> 05:39.472
COME ALONG, GIRLS,

05:39.472 --> 05:41.674
IT'S TIME WE WERE FINDING
OUR QUARTERS.

05:45.978 --> 05:48.481
De Long: THIS IS WHERE
WE WILL LIVE AND WORK.

05:48.481 --> 05:49.982
I DON'T KNOW.

05:49.982 --> 05:51.984
LOOKS MORE LIKE
A NUNNERY TO ME.

05:51.984 --> 05:53.986
VERY OBSERVANT,
MISS MacDONALD.

05:53.986 --> 05:55.988
THAT'S EXACTLY
WHAT IT WAS

05:55.988 --> 05:57.990
AND EXACTLY
HOW IT WILL STAY.

05:57.990 --> 05:59.992
NOW, IF YOU WILL
ALL FOLLOW ME,

05:59.992 --> 06:02.061
LET IT BE
CLEARLY UNDERSTOOD

06:02.061 --> 06:05.064
THAT ANY NURSE
CAUGHT FRATERNIZING
WITH THE PATIENTS

06:05.064 --> 06:07.133
WILL BE SENT HOME
IMMEDIATELY.

06:11.037 --> 06:12.939
YOU HAVE NO IDEA.

06:12.939 --> 06:14.040
WHAT?

06:14.040 --> 06:16.542
YOU HAVE TO STAND
WITH YOUR LEGS LIKE THIS.

06:16.542 --> 06:19.545
HOW DO THEY EXPECT YOU
TO MAKE IT FROM THAT SORT
OF DISTANCE?

06:19.545 --> 06:21.280
[GIGGLING]

06:22.882 --> 06:24.951
[OFFICER
COUNTING OUT MARCH]

06:30.556 --> 06:32.558
THEY LOOK GREAT,
DON'T THEY?

06:32.558 --> 06:35.061
LOOK AT IT
THIS WAY:

06:35.061 --> 06:38.064
WE SURE WON'T HAVE
TO WORRY ABOUT SPENDING
OUR HUGE PAYCHECKS

06:38.064 --> 06:40.566
'CAUSE THERE
AIN'T NO PLACE
TO SPEND 'EM.

06:40.566 --> 06:42.535
I THOUGHT
WE WERE GONNA BE

06:42.535 --> 06:44.036
IN SOME SORT
OF CITY.

06:44.036 --> 06:45.538
LOOKS LIKE ANYONE
UNDER 50

06:45.538 --> 06:47.039
IS JUST PASSING
THROUGH.

06:47.039 --> 06:49.041
WE GO WHERE
WE'RE SENT, ROSIE.

06:49.041 --> 06:51.544
I'M JUST GLAD
WE'RE SO CLOSE
TO THE FRONT.

06:51.544 --> 06:53.379
OH, NOT CLOSE ENOUGH
FOR ME.

06:53.379 --> 06:55.148
YEAH, WELL,
IF THE ITALIANS GET
PUSHED BACK AGAIN, AG,

06:55.148 --> 06:56.549
YOU'LL SOON
HAVE YOUR WISH.

06:56.549 --> 06:58.050
BUONA SERA, SIGNORINE.

06:58.050 --> 07:01.287
BENVENUTE NELLA NOSTRA
PICCOLE CITTADINE.

07:01.287 --> 07:04.624
THE LANGUAGE IS DEFINITELY
GONNA BE A PROBLEM HERE.

07:04.624 --> 07:08.127
BUT THESE ITALIAN GENTS
SURE ARE GALLANT,
AREN'T THEY?

07:08.127 --> 07:10.129
EVEN THE OLD COOTS.

07:10.129 --> 07:12.532
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT I READ ONCE?

07:12.532 --> 07:15.501
THAT ITALIAN MEN
RESPECT THEIR WIVES.

07:15.501 --> 07:17.003
THEY SPOIL
THEIR MISTRESSES.

07:17.003 --> 07:18.337
AGGIE.

07:18.337 --> 07:21.774
BUT THE ONLY WOMEN
THEY EVER REALLY LOVE
ARE THEIR MAMAS.

07:21.774 --> 07:22.909
[LAUGHTER]

07:22.909 --> 07:24.944
[MEN SCREAMING]

07:24.944 --> 07:28.114
Man: MAMA!

07:28.114 --> 07:30.183
[MEN YELLING]

07:31.117 --> 07:32.118
Man: ATTACCO!

07:32.118 --> 07:34.187
[GUNSHOTS]

07:36.456 --> 07:38.524
[MACHINE GUN FIRE]

07:47.033 --> 07:48.501
ATTACCO!

08:18.698 --> 08:20.199
Man: HELP ME.

08:20.199 --> 08:24.170
HELP ME, SOMEONE.

08:24.170 --> 08:26.672
[GROANING] HELP...

08:30.343 --> 08:32.245
[MOANING]

08:39.519 --> 08:41.587
[WHISTLITHE CAISSONS
GO ROLLING ALONG]

08:56.168 --> 08:57.169
♪ OVER HILL ♪

08:57.169 --> 08:58.671
♪ OVER DALE ♪

08:58.671 --> 09:01.073
♪ AS WE HIT
THE DUSTY TRAIL ♪

09:01.073 --> 09:04.644
♪ AND THOSE CAISSONS
GO ROLLING ALONG ♪

09:16.756 --> 09:18.257
HI, JIMMY!

09:18.257 --> 09:19.825
Jimmy:
HEY, HEY, ERNIE!

09:34.907 --> 09:36.375
WHERE'S BIRDSEED?

09:36.375 --> 09:37.877
BURNSIDE. HE'S IN THERE.
BUT YOU REALLY SHOULDN'T--

09:37.877 --> 09:38.878
I DIDN'T COME
ALL THIS WAY

09:38.878 --> 09:40.446
TO WAIT TABLES
BEHIND THE LINES.

09:40.446 --> 09:42.648
NOT WHY I SIGNED UP.
DON'T KNOW ABOUT YOU.

09:42.648 --> 09:43.716
OH, I DON'T KNOW.

09:43.716 --> 09:45.217
ALWAYS PLAY THE HAND
YOU'RE DEALT.

09:45.217 --> 09:46.218
THAT'S MY MOTTO.

09:46.218 --> 09:48.220
YEAH, WELL, REMIND ME
TO LOOK YOU UP

09:48.220 --> 09:51.357
WHEN I WANT A GOOD GAME
OF OLD MAID. WATCH THIS.

09:51.357 --> 09:53.225
SIR, LIEUTENANT
ERNEST HEMINGWAY

09:53.225 --> 09:55.728
REQUESTING A CHANGE
OF ASSIGNMENT.

09:55.728 --> 09:59.198
I WASN'T AWARE
LIEUTENANT HEMINGWAY
REPORTED FOR DUTY YET.

09:59.198 --> 10:01.667
SIR, LIEUTENANT HEMINGWAY
REPORTING FOR DUTY

10:01.667 --> 10:04.537
AND REQUESTING A CHANGE
OF ASSIGNMENT.

10:04.537 --> 10:05.538
Jimmy: ERNIE...

10:05.538 --> 10:07.039
THE ANSWER'S NO.

10:07.039 --> 10:08.307
SHALL WE?

10:08.307 --> 10:10.042
Italian Officer:
I AM GRATEFUL
FOR YOUR ASSISTANCE.

10:10.042 --> 10:11.711
Burnside: THAT'S WHY
WE'RE HERE, SIR.

10:11.711 --> 10:12.945
GRAZIE. CI VEDIAMO DOMANI.

10:12.945 --> 10:14.714
THANKS AGAIN
FOR COMING OVER.

10:14.714 --> 10:16.716
ARRIVEDERCI.

10:16.716 --> 10:18.217
NOW, YOUNG MAN,

10:18.217 --> 10:20.219
IF I WERE YOU,
I'D PUT ON AN APRON

10:20.219 --> 10:21.721
AND START SERVING
SOME COFFEE.

10:21.721 --> 10:23.189
YOU CAN'T DO THIS TO ME.
I'VE COME ALL THE WAY
FROM THE STATES.

10:23.189 --> 10:24.957
DO YOU KNOW WHAT THEY'RE
SAYING IN THE PAPERS?

10:24.957 --> 10:26.959
THIS IS THE WAR
TO END ALL WARS.

10:26.959 --> 10:29.228
IF I DON'T SEE ACTION NOW,
IT'LL BE TOO LATE.

10:29.228 --> 10:30.997
THIS IS MY LAST CHANCE.

10:30.997 --> 10:33.232
LET ME EXPLAIN
SOMETHING TO YOU,
HEMINGWAY.

10:33.232 --> 10:34.467
IF THE AMERICAN
RED CROSS WERE

10:34.467 --> 10:36.202
INTERESTED IN YOU
AS A FIGHTING MAN,

10:36.202 --> 10:38.704
THEY WOULD HAVE
ISSUED YOU A RIFLE,
IS THAT NOT SO?

10:38.704 --> 10:39.705
YES, SIR, BUT--

10:39.705 --> 10:41.273
BUT THEY DIDN'T DO THAT,
DID THEY?

10:41.273 --> 10:42.541
WELL, NO, SIR--

10:42.541 --> 10:44.410
AND YOUR JOB IS TO HELP
THE MORALE

10:44.410 --> 10:46.512
OF OUR WEARY
ITALIAN ALLIES.

10:46.512 --> 10:48.280
A SIMPLE CUP OF COFFEE.
A CIGARETTE.

10:48.280 --> 10:49.715
A CANDY BAR.

10:49.715 --> 10:51.717
A FEW WORDS
OF ENCOURAGEMENT.

10:51.717 --> 10:54.220
YES, SIR, I UNDERSTAND.
YOU ARE DEAD RIGHT, SIR.

10:54.220 --> 10:56.222
SIMPLE CUP OF COFFEE,
SOME CANDY,

10:56.222 --> 10:57.723
A PACK OF SMOKES.

10:57.723 --> 11:00.292
I SEE NOW THEY'RE SYMBOLS
OF SUPPORT AND ENCOURAGEMENT

11:00.292 --> 11:02.128
THAT CARRY THE SPIRIT
OF AMERICA

11:02.128 --> 11:03.963
TO OUR WAR-WEARY ALLIES
IN ITALY.

11:03.963 --> 11:05.965
AND WHERE ARE OUR COMRADES
THE MOST WEARY?

11:05.965 --> 11:07.933
WELL, IN THE FRONT LINE,
RIGHT, SIR?

11:07.933 --> 11:09.935
IN THE TRENCHES,
RIGHT, SIR?

11:09.935 --> 11:11.437
YOU'RE WRONG, JIMMY.

11:11.437 --> 11:13.439
BIRDSEED'S NOT NEARLY
THE HORSE'S ASS
YOU SAID HE WAS.

11:13.439 --> 11:15.141
I'LL GET MY BAG, SIR.

11:15.141 --> 11:16.642
SEE YOU, JIMMY.

11:16.642 --> 11:18.344
McBRIDE.

11:21.781 --> 11:23.849
[EXPLOSIONS
IN THE DISTANCE]

11:28.120 --> 11:30.189
[EXPLOSIONS GROW LOUDER]

11:33.459 --> 11:35.528
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

11:37.797 --> 11:39.365
Ernest: BUONA SERA.

12:20.039 --> 12:21.340
BUONA SERA.

12:21.340 --> 12:23.843
DOES, UH...ANYONE--

12:23.843 --> 12:26.846
ANY OF YOU SPEAK
INGLESE? ENGLISH?

12:26.846 --> 12:28.347
UN POCO.

12:28.347 --> 12:29.682
ERNIE HEMINGWAY.

12:29.682 --> 12:31.350
NEWSPAPER REPORTER
FROM KANSAS CITY.

12:31.350 --> 12:32.852
VOUI UN CAFFE?

12:32.852 --> 12:34.353
NO. NO, THANK YOU.

12:34.353 --> 12:35.688
ENRICO BISCAGLIA.

12:35.688 --> 12:37.690
I AM A WAITER
FROM BORDIGHERA.

12:37.690 --> 12:39.191
HERE YOU GO. CIGARETTE?

12:39.191 --> 12:41.193
HOW LONG YOU BEEN HERE?

12:41.193 --> 12:43.829
FRANCESCO, ME,
WE 2 MONTHS.

12:43.829 --> 12:45.364
ROBERTO DUE,
TRE SETTIMANE.

12:45.364 --> 12:46.599
2, 3 WEEKS.

12:48.167 --> 12:49.835
COULD YOU PLEASE...

12:49.835 --> 12:52.338
ASK ROBERTO "COULD
I SEE HIS RIFLE?"

12:52.338 --> 12:54.774
MOSTRA IL TUO FUCILE
AL GIORNALISTA AMERICANO.

12:54.774 --> 12:57.343
[EXPLOSIONS OUTSIDE]

12:58.511 --> 13:00.146
AVANTI.
FAGLIELO VERDERE.

13:00.146 --> 13:02.281
[LOCKS SAFETY]

13:03.916 --> 13:05.417
THAT'S A PEACH.

13:05.417 --> 13:06.919
E' UNA PESCA.

13:06.919 --> 13:08.420
Roberto: UNA PESCA?

13:08.420 --> 13:10.923
E QUELIO CHE HA DETTO.
IT'S A PEACH.

13:10.923 --> 13:13.425
COSA CREDI CHE NON SAPPIA
COME SI DICE PESCA?

13:13.425 --> 13:15.728
QUESTA...

13:15.728 --> 13:17.930
NON E UNA PESCA.

13:17.930 --> 13:20.533
E' UN FUCILE.

13:20.533 --> 13:22.401
CAPITO? FUCILE.

13:22.401 --> 13:23.402
FUCILE.

13:23.402 --> 13:25.171
Enrico:
HE TELL YOU "RIFLE."

13:25.171 --> 13:26.238
FUCILE.

13:27.206 --> 13:29.241
AH, SI, FUCILE.

13:29.241 --> 13:31.243
[EXPLOSIONS OUTSIDE]

13:31.243 --> 13:34.413
THE, UH, AUSTRIANS--
THROUGH THERE?

13:34.413 --> 13:35.915
Enrico: EH, SI, SI.

13:35.915 --> 13:38.484
ON THE OTHER SIDE
OF THE RIDGE.

13:40.619 --> 13:42.988
[MAKING GUN NOISES]

13:47.560 --> 13:49.428
GRAZIE.

13:49.428 --> 13:51.096
YOU, UH, ARDITI,
RIGHT?

13:51.096 --> 13:52.431
SI, ARDITI.

13:52.431 --> 13:53.933
WE ARE THE BEST.

13:53.933 --> 13:55.634
ARDIIS THE BEST.

13:55.634 --> 13:57.703
SALUTE. ENRICO,
VOI RESTATE QUI?

13:57.703 --> 13:59.538
SI, SI. ANDATE.

13:59.538 --> 14:02.441
VENITE, RAGAZZI.
ANDIAMO! SIAMO PRONTI.

14:02.441 --> 14:05.444
WHAT DO
YOU FELLAS THINK ABOUT
WHILE YOU'RE WAITING?

14:05.444 --> 14:06.946
I THINK OF ROSARIES--

14:06.946 --> 14:09.849
HOW MANY I HAVE TO SAY
IF GOD LET ME LIVE.

14:11.283 --> 14:12.651
ROBERTO...

14:12.651 --> 14:15.654
HE THINK OF WOMEN
ALL THE TIME.

14:15.654 --> 14:17.923
THAT'S BECAUSE
HE'S NOT HAD ONE YET.

14:18.958 --> 14:20.292
NO DAMAS?

14:20.292 --> 14:21.794
NO, NO UNO?

14:21.794 --> 14:23.629
NO UNO.

14:23.629 --> 14:26.065
AND YOU,
BAMBINO AMERICANO?

14:26.065 --> 14:27.066
PLENTY.

14:27.066 --> 14:28.267
MUCHO DAMAS.

14:28.267 --> 14:29.768
MANY WOMEN.

14:29.768 --> 14:31.270
Enrico: DICE BUGIE, EH?

14:31.270 --> 14:33.272
I THINK YOU TELL LIES.

14:33.272 --> 14:34.773
[LOUD EXPLOSION]

14:34.773 --> 14:37.276
Enrico: WHY YOU NOT
A SOLDIER?

14:37.276 --> 14:38.777
TRIED MY DAMNEDEST,

14:38.777 --> 14:40.279
BUT THEY WOULDN'T
TAKE ME.

14:40.279 --> 14:41.280
Enrico: "DAMNEDEST"?

14:41.280 --> 14:42.381
UH, NO POSSIBILE.

14:42.381 --> 14:43.782
NOT POSSIBLE.

14:43.782 --> 14:46.051
WHY, TOO YOUNG?

14:46.051 --> 14:47.720
Man: RAGAZZI, SIETE PRONTI?
ABBIAMO UN MINUTE AL...

14:47.720 --> 14:49.321
L'EMETTO.

14:49.321 --> 14:52.391
NO--NO, I--I--I
LIED ABOUT MY AGE.

14:53.459 --> 14:54.960
IT'S MY LEFT EYE.

14:54.960 --> 14:56.795
MY LEFT EYE,
IT'S NO GOOD.

14:56.795 --> 14:58.397
IT, UH--TOO MUCH BOXING.

14:58.397 --> 15:00.299
UH, L'ESERCITO
NON SE LO PIGLIAVA

15:00.299 --> 15:02.301
PERCHE A GUERCIO
DALL'OCCHIO SINISTRO.

15:02.301 --> 15:05.504
MEGLIO L'OCCHIO SINISTRO
CHE IL COGLIONE SINISTRO.

15:05.504 --> 15:07.640
[MEN LAUGHING]

15:07.640 --> 15:09.341
ROBERTO SAY

15:09.341 --> 15:11.343
BETTER YOUR LEFT EYE...

15:11.343 --> 15:12.711
THAN YOUR LEFT BALL.

15:12.711 --> 15:14.179
[ARTILLERY SHELL
WHISTLING]

15:28.527 --> 15:29.528
AH.

15:29.528 --> 15:30.529
[COUGHS]

15:30.529 --> 15:31.530
OH.

15:31.530 --> 15:32.698
AAH.

15:32.698 --> 15:34.400
[COUGHING]

15:34.400 --> 15:35.668
OH, GOD.

15:39.338 --> 15:40.839
AAH!

15:40.839 --> 15:42.074
AAH.

15:58.590 --> 15:59.591
OH.

15:59.591 --> 16:01.794
Roberto: AIUTO.

16:05.597 --> 16:06.765
ROBERTO.

16:07.700 --> 16:09.468
Roberto: AIUTO.

16:10.402 --> 16:11.971
ROBERTO.

16:12.905 --> 16:14.406
ROBERTO.

16:14.406 --> 16:15.908
OH, GOD.

16:15.908 --> 16:17.977
[GRUNTING]

16:27.920 --> 16:28.988
AAH.

16:37.262 --> 16:38.497
OK.

16:40.899 --> 16:42.668
[FLARES HISS]

17:08.993 --> 17:10.561
[MACHINE GUN FIRE]

17:11.497 --> 17:12.897
AAH!

17:19.972 --> 17:21.707
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

17:25.344 --> 17:26.545
UHH.

17:26.545 --> 17:29.615
[CLOTH RIPPING]

17:30.983 --> 17:32.317
UHH.

17:32.317 --> 17:33.919
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

17:43.595 --> 17:44.997
[GROANING]

17:48.333 --> 17:49.835
UHH!

17:49.835 --> 17:51.570
AAH!

17:51.570 --> 17:53.305
UHH!

17:57.476 --> 17:59.478
THAT SAY...

17:59.478 --> 18:01.547
DOES THAT SAY
I'M GONNA LIVE,

18:01.547 --> 18:03.549
OR DOES IT SAY
I'M GONNA DIE?

18:03.549 --> 18:05.617
BAMBINO AMERICANO.

18:06.652 --> 18:07.820
ROBERTO.

18:07.820 --> 18:10.889
SI E BUONO.

18:12.191 --> 18:13.892
GOOD.

18:13.892 --> 18:15.794
HEY, I'M FINE.
I'M FINE. HELP HIM.

18:15.794 --> 18:17.796
HE'S NEVER EVEN
BEEN WITH A WOMAN.

18:17.796 --> 18:18.797
CALMA.

18:18.797 --> 18:20.299
DAMN IT!

18:20.299 --> 18:21.533
YOU BASTARDS!

18:21.533 --> 18:23.035
DON'T LET HIM DIE!

18:23.035 --> 18:24.970
WE GO TO HIM.

18:43.222 --> 18:44.556
IS EVERYBODY HERE?

18:44.556 --> 18:45.858
YES, MISS DE LONG.

18:45.858 --> 18:48.360
APPARENTLY, IT'S NOT
A MAJOR EMERGENCY,
AFTER ALL,

18:48.360 --> 18:51.063
SO WE WON'T
NEED EXTRA PEOPLE ON
THE MORNING SHIFT.

18:51.063 --> 18:53.565
BUT WE WILL HAVE
SEVERAL CASUALTIES
WITHIN THE HOUR,

18:53.565 --> 18:55.300
SO YOU ALL KNOW
THE ROUTINE.

18:55.300 --> 18:56.535
COME ON DOWNSTAIRS.

18:56.535 --> 18:57.703
ALL RIGHT.

18:57.703 --> 18:59.037
YOU'RE WITH ME.

18:59.037 --> 19:01.273
[KLAXON HONKING]

19:05.611 --> 19:08.147
[HONK]

19:10.115 --> 19:11.717
COME ON, COME ON.

19:11.717 --> 19:13.118
Nurse:
TAKE IT EASY.

19:13.118 --> 19:14.520
PIANO, PIANO.

19:23.729 --> 19:26.632
De Long:
WE'LL PUT HIM
IN NUMBER 8. OTTO.

19:26.632 --> 19:29.101
AND THIS ONE IN
NUMBER 9, MISS ROSE.

19:29.101 --> 19:31.103
Skip: THIS LAST ONE
MUST BE CRAZY.

19:31.103 --> 19:32.871
CARRIED ONE OF
THE ARDITI WOUNDED

19:32.871 --> 19:34.106
RIGHT THROUGH
A BOMBARDMENT.

19:34.106 --> 19:36.008
YES, MA'AM?
IN THAT CASE--
UH, MISS CAVANAUGH?

19:36.008 --> 19:38.110
WE'LL PUT HIM AT
THE FAR END, WHERE
IT'S QUIETER. IN 17.

19:38.110 --> 19:39.244
YES, MA'AM.

19:39.244 --> 19:40.245
DICIASETTE.

19:40.245 --> 19:41.580
HO CAPITO,
SIGNORA.

19:41.580 --> 19:42.781
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED?

19:42.781 --> 19:45.117
IT'S A BAD LEG WOUND.
HE GOT IT ON THE PIAVE FRONT.

19:46.185 --> 19:47.419
LIFT.

19:53.692 --> 19:55.360
ANYTHING YOU NEED?

19:55.360 --> 19:58.096
I'LL NEED, UH,
MORE SALINE SOLUTION.

20:04.670 --> 20:05.837
HEY, KID.

20:05.837 --> 20:07.673
AM I DYING?

20:07.673 --> 20:09.341
OH, EVENTUALLY,

20:09.341 --> 20:12.344
BUT NOT IN
THE IMMEDIATE FUTURE.

20:12.344 --> 20:13.845
YOU LYING TO ME?

20:13.845 --> 20:15.847
MM-MM.

20:15.847 --> 20:17.849
YOU PROMISE?

20:17.849 --> 20:19.351
PROMISE.

20:28.460 --> 20:30.128
I LOVE YOU.

20:31.463 --> 20:33.365
WILL YOU MARRY ME?

20:53.452 --> 20:55.187
HOW WE FEELING?

21:25.284 --> 21:27.419
WHAT'S WRONG?

21:27.419 --> 21:29.421
HMM? NOTHING.

21:29.421 --> 21:32.524
MAC, WOULD YOU COME
OVER HERE FOR A MINUTE?

21:32.524 --> 21:35.694
SOME-SOMETHING'S
THE MATTER. WHAT IS IT?

21:37.229 --> 21:38.730
WELL?

21:38.730 --> 21:40.699
LIKE I SAID, KID,
NOTHING'S WRONG.

21:40.699 --> 21:42.567
I'M JUST GIVING
BED 8 A DRINK.

21:42.567 --> 21:45.604
YEAH, BUT
WHAT'S GOING ON?

21:47.673 --> 21:49.741
I'LL BE BACK
IN A MINUTE.

21:52.477 --> 21:54.212
GANGRENE?

21:54.212 --> 21:55.380
MAYBE.

21:55.380 --> 21:57.049
CAN WE GET A DOCTOR?

21:57.049 --> 21:58.383
NOT UNTIL TOMORROW.

21:58.383 --> 22:00.385
IT MIGHT BE
TOO LATE BY THEN.

22:00.385 --> 22:01.787
I CAN'T HELP IT.

22:01.787 --> 22:04.289
MISS DE LONG
SAID THE ONLY DOCTOR
THE ITALIANS COULD SPARE

22:04.289 --> 22:06.124
WOULDN'T BE HERE
TILL TOMORROW.

22:06.124 --> 22:07.793
HMM, HMM.

22:07.793 --> 22:09.795
YOU KNOW,
THE ONLY THING TO DO

22:09.795 --> 22:11.797
IS IRRIGATE THE WOUND
WITH DAKEN'S.

22:11.797 --> 22:13.765
NO. YOU CANNOT DO
SOMETHING LIKE THAT

22:13.765 --> 22:15.767
WITHOUT
A DOCTOR'S ORDER.

22:15.767 --> 22:18.937
MAC, WE CAN'T WAIT
FOR A DOCTOR'S ORDER.

22:18.937 --> 22:20.439
AGGIE,
SOMETHING LIKE THAT

22:20.439 --> 22:22.507
COULD GET YOU SHIPPED
BACK TO THE STATES.

22:22.507 --> 22:25.010
FINE. I WON'T BE DOING
THE SPLITS WHEN I GO
TO THE BATHROOM.

22:25.010 --> 22:26.244
AG!

22:37.122 --> 22:38.623
GOOD AFTERNOON, DOCTOR.

22:38.623 --> 22:41.626
I'VE BEEN ASSIGNED AS
YOUR SURGICAL ASSISTANT.

22:41.626 --> 22:42.928
MAJOR CARACCIOLO.

22:42.928 --> 22:45.063
AGNES VON KUROWSKY.

22:45.063 --> 22:46.798
AH, YES, HEMINGWAY.

22:46.798 --> 22:49.134
SHRAPNEL EVERYWHERE.

22:50.268 --> 22:52.771
SOME QUITE DEEP.

22:52.771 --> 22:54.373
COME, COME.

22:56.775 --> 22:58.877
BULLET BEHIND
THE PATELLA.

22:59.878 --> 23:02.447
DID YOU SEE
ANY PIECES OF--

23:02.447 --> 23:04.950
COME SI DICE?

23:04.950 --> 23:06.351
UH, UNIFORM.

23:06.351 --> 23:08.019
OH, YES, THANK YOU.
UNIFORM.

23:08.019 --> 23:10.122
DID YOU SEE ANY UNIFORM
IN THE WOUND?

23:10.122 --> 23:12.357
UNFORTUNATELY, YES.

23:12.357 --> 23:14.359
AND WHEN I WAS
CHANGING THE DRESSING

23:14.359 --> 23:16.361
LAST NIGHT AND THEN
AGAIN THIS MORNING,

23:16.361 --> 23:18.530
THERE WAS A DEFINITE ODOR.

23:18.530 --> 23:20.031
GANGRENE.

23:20.031 --> 23:22.000
SO IF IT IS,

23:22.000 --> 23:24.736
I WILL HAVE
TO AMPUTATE.

23:25.837 --> 23:27.839
I WILL OPERATE
ON THIS SIDE

23:27.839 --> 23:31.042
WITH A NURSE,
YOU, ON MY LEFT.

23:35.847 --> 23:39.751
YOU DO NOT APPROVE
OF AN AMPUTATION?

23:43.054 --> 23:47.159
I THINK HE IS VERY YOUNG
TO LOSE A LEG.

23:47.159 --> 23:49.327
ECCO.

23:49.327 --> 23:51.930
YOU SEE? I WAS RIGHT.

23:51.930 --> 23:53.965
AND HOW DO YOU PROPOSE

23:53.965 --> 23:56.835
THAT WE SHALL NOT
HAVE TO AMPUTATE

23:56.835 --> 23:59.237
THIS YOUNG BOY'S LEG?

24:00.439 --> 24:03.275
WELL, IN AMERICA,
WE'VE HAD SOME SUCCESS

24:03.275 --> 24:06.278
WITH A TREATMENT
THAT WAS DEVELOPED
AT JOHNS HOPKINS HOSPITAL,

24:06.278 --> 24:08.280
SO I'VE BEEN
IRRIGATING THE WOUND--

24:08.280 --> 24:11.683
I KNOW EVERYTHING
ABOUT THIS NOTION
OF IRRIGATING.

24:12.918 --> 24:15.420
WHO IS
THIS JOHN HOPKINS
OF THE HOSPITAL?

24:15.420 --> 24:17.789
IS HE A SAINT?

24:17.789 --> 24:23.261
IT'S JOHNS HOPKINS,
AND, NO, IT'S NOT NAMED
AFTER A SAINT.

24:23.261 --> 24:26.498
THEN IT CANNOT BE
MUCH OF A HOSPITAL,
CAN IT?

24:28.200 --> 24:31.903
WELL, I WILL OPERATE
TOMORROW IN THE MORNING.

24:31.903 --> 24:34.406
PLEASE HAVE THE PATIENT
READY AT 8:30.

24:34.406 --> 24:36.508
AND, NURSE...

24:36.508 --> 24:41.313
PERHAPS YOU WOULD LIKE
MY PERMISSION FOR YOUR
IRRIGATION TREATMENT.

24:53.058 --> 24:56.161
BEAUTIFUL GIRL
WITH A MARTINI.

24:56.161 --> 24:58.997
I MUST HAVE DIED
AND GONE TO HEAVEN.

25:04.135 --> 25:05.971
GIN AND CASTOR OIL.

25:05.971 --> 25:07.973
SORRY ABOUT THAT.

25:07.973 --> 25:12.277
OHH.

25:14.613 --> 25:16.882
WHAT DO YOU KNOW?

25:16.882 --> 25:18.884
I GRADUATED
THE SAME YEAR.

25:18.884 --> 25:21.052
MM-HMM. ME FROM
NURSING SCHOOL,

25:21.052 --> 25:23.855
YOU FROM
KINDERGARTEN?

25:23.855 --> 25:26.725
MY MOTHER TOLD ME
NEVER ASK A LADY

25:26.725 --> 25:28.727
ABOUT HER AGE
OR HER TEETH.

25:28.727 --> 25:32.130
MMM. 26, AND THEY'RE
ALL MINE.

25:37.536 --> 25:39.871
WHAT'S GOING ON?

25:39.871 --> 25:43.041
I'M GOING TO IRRIGATE
THE WOUND AGAIN.

25:44.209 --> 25:46.211
RELAX. RELAX.

25:46.211 --> 25:47.746
MMM!

25:51.716 --> 25:53.952
GANGRENE?

25:58.223 --> 26:01.359
NOW, HOW DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT GANGRENE?

26:01.359 --> 26:04.129
MY OLD MAN'S A DOCTOR.

26:04.129 --> 26:06.965
AND AFTER THE WAR, YOU'RE
GOING TO MEDICAL SCHOOL.

26:06.965 --> 26:08.767
NOT A CHANCE.

26:08.767 --> 26:10.769
I'M A REPORTER.

26:10.769 --> 26:12.103
A REPORTER?

26:12.103 --> 26:13.838
HOW OLD ARE YOU?

26:15.440 --> 26:17.409
22.

26:17.409 --> 26:22.647
KID, I HOPE YOU'RE
A BETTER REPORTER
THAN YOU ARE A LIAR.

26:22.647 --> 26:25.951
RELAX.

26:32.290 --> 26:34.759
AM I GOING
TO LOSE MY LEG?

26:39.464 --> 26:41.933
I'M ASKING YOU,
PLEASE.

26:41.933 --> 26:45.270
I'M REALLY NOT PERMITTED
TO TALK ABOUT YOUR CONDITION.

26:45.270 --> 26:49.007
YOU...YOU'LL HAVE TO
SPEAK WITH THE SURGEON.

26:50.942 --> 26:53.044
SURGEON?

26:55.046 --> 26:58.283
IF I'M GOING
TO END UP BEING

26:58.283 --> 27:00.585
LESS THAN
ALL OF ME...

27:02.687 --> 27:04.589
I'D RATHER BE DEAD.

27:10.195 --> 27:13.932
KID, I'M GOING
TO DO EVERYTHING I CAN
TO HELP YOU KEEP YOUR LEG.

27:15.500 --> 27:18.970
BUT YOU'RE GOING
TO HAVE TO WORK WITH ME.

27:21.806 --> 27:26.111
I'M GOING TO KEEP ON
WASHING OUT THIS WOUND
WITH DAKEN'S ACID

27:26.111 --> 27:28.279
EVERY HOUR
ON THE HOUR.

27:28.279 --> 27:31.249
YOU'LL BE UP AND
DANCING IN NO TIME.

27:32.851 --> 27:35.420
I'M NOT A VERY
GOOD DANCER.

27:36.688 --> 27:38.690
BIG FEET
AND NO RHYTHM.

27:38.690 --> 27:40.358
[CHUCKLES]

27:40.358 --> 27:42.861
WELL, I AM.

27:42.861 --> 27:45.363
I LOVE TO DANCE.

27:45.363 --> 27:50.035
I'LL TEACH YOU
AND GET YOU GOOD AND READY
FOR THE GIRLS BACK HOME.

27:50.035 --> 27:51.569
[LIQUID SQUIRTING]

27:58.343 --> 28:00.645
UNO, DUE, TRE.

28:10.889 --> 28:12.557
Ernest: ROSIE?

28:12.557 --> 28:15.493
DON'T PUT ME UNDER YET.

28:16.594 --> 28:18.363
WHERE'S AGNES?

28:18.363 --> 28:19.998
SHE'S RIGHT HERE.

28:24.936 --> 28:27.539
JESUS, I'M SCARED.

28:27.539 --> 28:30.175
YOU AND ME, PARTNER.

28:30.175 --> 28:31.676
GOOD MORNING,
YOUNG MAN.

28:31.676 --> 28:33.511
MORNING, DOC.

28:33.511 --> 28:35.413
YOU GOTTA PROMISE
ME ONE THING.

28:35.413 --> 28:36.948
SAVE THE BULLET
FOR ME.

28:36.948 --> 28:39.884
YES, OF COURSE.

28:39.884 --> 28:41.419
[GAS HISSING]

28:41.419 --> 28:43.354
Agnes: BREATHE DEEPLY.

29:00.472 --> 29:01.706
HMM.

29:01.706 --> 29:03.007
WELL...

29:04.976 --> 29:08.480
I DO NOT SMELL THE ODOR
YOU SPOKE ABOUT YESTERDAY,

29:08.480 --> 29:13.551
BUT IT WOULD...STILL BE
SAFEST TO AMPUTATE NOW.

29:17.655 --> 29:19.257
I'M SORRY.

29:19.257 --> 29:21.760
BEING SAFE IS NOT
IMPORTANT TO HIM,
DOCTOR.

29:21.760 --> 29:23.762
HE WANTS TO
KEEP HIS LEG.

29:23.762 --> 29:26.831
AHEM.
JILL, THE LARGER
SPONGES, PLEASE.

29:28.967 --> 29:30.135
THANK YOU.

29:30.135 --> 29:32.637
AS I'M SURE YOU KNOW,

29:32.637 --> 29:35.974
SECOND OPERATIONS
ARE A GREAT LUXURY

29:35.974 --> 29:37.475
IN TIME OF WAR.

29:37.475 --> 29:39.043
YES, OF COURSE.

29:45.984 --> 29:47.986
BUT ONE COULD SAY,

29:47.986 --> 29:52.323
WHAT IS LIFE WITHOUT
ITS LITTLE LUXURIES?

29:54.993 --> 29:58.229
REFRACTOR
AND LONG FORCEPS.

30:09.240 --> 30:11.743
HOLY COW,
HE'S GOOD-LOOKING.

30:11.743 --> 30:13.411
YEAH...

30:13.411 --> 30:15.346
BUT YOUNG.

30:15.346 --> 30:17.482
I MEANT
DR. CARACCIOLO.

30:17.482 --> 30:20.084
Caracciolo:
MISS VON KUROWSKY?

30:21.986 --> 30:24.656
PERHAPS ONE DAY
YOU WILL PERMIT ME

30:24.656 --> 30:27.292
TO SHOW YOU
SOMETHING OF
OUR COUNTRYSIDE...

30:29.861 --> 30:32.630
WHEN YOU WILL
BE OFF DUTY.

30:41.472 --> 30:43.708
I THINK I HATE YOU.

30:53.084 --> 30:54.485
MMM.

30:58.990 --> 31:01.559
EVERYTHING IS FINE.

31:01.559 --> 31:04.128
YOU'RE GOING
TO KEEP YOUR LEG.

31:06.064 --> 31:07.632
SLEEP.

31:42.033 --> 31:45.770
I DON'T WANT TO DANCE
WITH THE GIRLS BACK HOME.

31:57.215 --> 32:00.718
BED 8's
AN INTERESTING CASE.

32:00.718 --> 32:03.788
THOUGHT YESTERDAY
THERE MIGHT BE SOME
PERIPHERAL VISION

32:03.788 --> 32:05.857
IN THE LEFT EYE.

32:08.626 --> 32:11.629
IT'S STILL EARLY,
OF COURSE.

32:11.629 --> 32:13.298
[SIGHS]

32:13.298 --> 32:17.268
ARE THEY ALWAYS JUST
CASES TO YOU, MAC?

32:17.268 --> 32:20.772
IT'S THE ONLY WAY
TO COPE.

32:20.772 --> 32:23.775
YOU SHOULD KNOW THAT
AS WELL AS I DO.

32:23.775 --> 32:27.111
WELL, I DO KNOW IT WITH
ONE PART OF MY BRAIN,

32:27.111 --> 32:28.680
BUT SOMETIMES...

32:28.680 --> 32:31.683
SOMETIMES
THEY GET TO YOU.

32:31.683 --> 32:35.687
ESPECIALLY WHEN THEY'RE
GOOD-LOOKING BOYS WITH
THE CHARM OF THE DEVIL,

32:35.687 --> 32:37.689
AND YOU'VE BROKEN
ALL THE RULES

32:37.689 --> 32:41.693
TO MAKE SURE
THEY WALK OUT OF HERE
ON BOTH LEGS.

32:41.693 --> 32:44.095
BUT JUST REMEMBER...

32:44.095 --> 32:46.731
WE'RE HERE TO DO A JOB.
WE'RE HERE TO DO A JOB.

32:49.267 --> 32:51.102
FOR GOD'S SAKE,
BE CAREFUL.

32:51.102 --> 32:53.604
[KLAXON HONKS]

32:53.604 --> 32:56.207
[HONK]

32:57.608 --> 33:00.111
De Long: VILLARD IN 15,
QUINDICI.

33:00.111 --> 33:02.180
KENYON IN 13, TREDICI.

33:02.180 --> 33:04.682
[WHISTLITHE CAISSONS
GO ROLLING ALONG]

33:04.682 --> 33:07.185
De Long:
MR. McBRIDE IN 6
NEEDS IMMEDIATE ATTENTION.

33:07.185 --> 33:10.254
WE'RE SHORT OF DOCTORS,
BUT I'VE TELEPHONED ALREADY.

33:11.689 --> 33:14.826
THIS IS VILLARD, HENRY S.,
IN 15?

33:14.826 --> 33:16.327
YES, MISS DE LONG.

33:16.327 --> 33:17.695
HARRY VILLARD?

33:17.695 --> 33:19.163
HEY, YOU HARVARD
YARD BASTARD,

33:19.163 --> 33:20.665
HOW THE HELL
ARE YOU?

33:20.665 --> 33:24.168
MR. HEMINGWAY, I WILL
NOT TOLERATE THAT KIND
OF LANGUAGE ON MY WARD.

33:24.168 --> 33:26.170
Harry: IF THAT'S
ERNEST HEMINGWAY, MA'AM,

33:26.170 --> 33:28.172
BAD LANGUAGE IS THE LEAST
OF YOUR PROBLEMS.

33:28.172 --> 33:30.274
HE'S GOT CHRONIC
DIARRHEA OF THE MOUTH.

33:30.274 --> 33:31.676
MR. VILLARD!

33:31.676 --> 33:33.745
WHAT ARE YOU
IN HERE FOR, HARRY?

33:35.279 --> 33:36.781
WELL,
WHATEVER IT IS,

33:36.781 --> 33:39.217
THESE GALS WILL HAVE
YOU BACK IN THE PINK
IN NO TIME.

33:40.685 --> 33:43.554
UH, MAYBE NOT.

33:43.554 --> 33:45.356
AT LEAST YELLOW'S
MORE BECOMING THAN
THAT CUTE--

33:45.356 --> 33:47.392
De Long: JAUNDICE
IS NO LAUGHING MATTER,

33:47.392 --> 33:49.961
AND IF YOU
BOTHER MR. VILLARD,
I'LL HAVE YOU MOVED.

33:51.562 --> 33:53.297
WE CALL HER GUMSHOE.

33:56.167 --> 33:58.503
I SEE YOU WERE HIT.

33:58.503 --> 34:00.004
YEAH.

34:00.004 --> 34:01.572
WHERE WERE YOU?

34:01.572 --> 34:04.575
ON THE PIAVE. YOU?

34:04.575 --> 34:07.345
I WAS AT GRAPPA.

34:07.345 --> 34:09.647
WAS IT BAD?

34:10.882 --> 34:12.315
BAD.

34:13.751 --> 34:15.152
ME, TOO.

34:17.288 --> 34:20.291
IS THERE
A NURSE VON KUROWSKY
STILL HERE?

34:20.291 --> 34:21.426
AGNES?

34:23.761 --> 34:27.231
I'LL LET YOU DOWN
FAST, OLD SPORT.
SHE'S SPOKEN FOR.

34:27.231 --> 34:30.735
OH, NO.
I--I SAW HER FIRST.
I DROVE HER HERE.

34:30.735 --> 34:32.737
FOR WHICH WE ARE
TRULY THANKFUL.

34:32.737 --> 34:34.806
ANYWAY, SHE NEEDS
A REAL MAN.

34:34.806 --> 34:36.306
WHY IS PRECISELY WHY

34:36.306 --> 34:39.243
SHE WOULD NEVER GO
FOR A CONCEITED WINDBAG
LIKE YOURSELF.

34:39.243 --> 34:40.745
Man: NO!

34:40.745 --> 34:42.713
PLEASE!

34:42.713 --> 34:43.748
DON'T! OHH!

34:43.748 --> 34:45.616
JESUS, WHAT
HAPPENED TO HIM?

34:45.616 --> 34:47.652
HIT BY A PHOSPHOROUS SHELL

34:47.652 --> 34:50.755
HANDING OUT CANDY BARS
AT THE PIAVE CANTEEN.

34:50.755 --> 34:52.255
Man: AAH! AAH!

34:52.255 --> 34:54.257
JESUS CHRIST!
JIMMY?

34:54.257 --> 34:55.525
Man: AAH! AAH!

34:55.525 --> 34:57.395
WE WERE THERE
TOGETHER.

34:57.395 --> 34:59.597
De Long: STILL!
KEEP STILL, SON!

34:59.597 --> 35:00.798
Man: AAH!

35:00.798 --> 35:01.999
WHAT IS IT?
WHAT IS IT?

35:01.999 --> 35:03.501
De Long: WE'LL
LEAVE THE DRESSING

35:03.501 --> 35:05.303
UNTIL WE GIVE YOU
SOMETHING FOR THE PAIN.

35:05.303 --> 35:07.371
Burton: WHAT'S
HAPPENING TO HIM?

35:19.917 --> 35:22.386
JIMMY,
IT'S ERNIE.

35:23.321 --> 35:27.525
ERNIE.

35:27.525 --> 35:30.027
YOU'RE GONNA
BE ALL RIGHT.

35:30.027 --> 35:31.562
YOU UNDERSTAND?

35:33.297 --> 35:34.866
I PROMISE YOU.

35:37.802 --> 35:39.303
YOU'LL BE FINE.

35:39.303 --> 35:40.705
[JIMMY WHIMPERS]

35:48.813 --> 35:51.315
BUONA SERA.

35:51.315 --> 35:52.817
PER LEI.

35:52.817 --> 35:54.252
GRAZIE.

36:00.892 --> 36:03.127
[FOOTSTEPS RUNNING PAST]

36:13.538 --> 36:16.874
YOU REALLY SHOULDN'T
BE IN HERE, KID.

36:16.874 --> 36:19.877
ERNIE.
MY NAME'S ERNIE.

36:19.877 --> 36:22.580
WHATEVER YOU SAY...
KID.

36:22.580 --> 36:26.083
"TO DR. JAMES PAXTON,
BELLEVUE HOSPITAL."

36:26.083 --> 36:34.892
"DR. JAMES PAXTON,
BELLEVUE HOSPITAL."

36:34.892 --> 36:36.894
AND I DON'T SUPPOSE
IT EVER OCCURRED TO YOU

36:36.894 --> 36:39.063
THAT THOSE
MIGHT BE PERSONAL?

36:46.871 --> 36:50.875
LAST NIGHT, A BUNCH
OF US WERE TALKING
ABOUT WHY WE CAME HERE.

36:50.875 --> 36:54.378
AND I SAID THAT I CAME
HERE BECAUSE I WAS
LOOKING FOR SOMETHING.

36:54.378 --> 36:55.880
HMM.

36:55.880 --> 36:58.549
I'M NOT SURE
WHAT IT IS...

36:58.549 --> 37:00.751
BUT I KNOW
I'LL FIND IT HERE.

37:03.287 --> 37:07.792
SOMEWHERE ABOUT
6 MILES FROM HERE
IN THE TRENCHES,

37:07.792 --> 37:10.027
THAT'S WHERE IT IS.

37:14.432 --> 37:17.568
IT NEVER OCCURRED
TO ME UNTIL NOW

37:17.568 --> 37:19.937
THAT IT MIGHT
BE POSSIBLE

37:19.937 --> 37:22.873
TO COME HERE LOOKING TO
GET AWAY FROM SOMETHING.

37:28.446 --> 37:30.181
TOUCHá.

37:35.453 --> 37:37.622
IT'S NO USE
HIM WRITING YOU,
YOU KNOW.

37:37.622 --> 37:39.123
HMM.

37:39.123 --> 37:41.125
'CAUSE YOU'RE
IN LOVE WITH ME.

37:41.125 --> 37:42.727
OH. HA HA HA.

37:42.727 --> 37:44.228
I AM, AM I?

37:44.228 --> 37:45.730
MMM.
YEAH.

37:46.931 --> 37:49.000
YOU JUST DON'T
KNOW IT YET.

37:50.034 --> 37:53.604
WILL YOU GET OUT
OF HERE, KID? PLEASE?

38:12.290 --> 38:13.824
GOOD MORNING,
MISS AGNES.

38:13.824 --> 38:14.825
GOOD MORNING.

38:14.825 --> 38:16.460
AG.

38:16.460 --> 38:18.229
MAY I PRESENT
YOU MY ADJUTANT,

38:18.229 --> 38:19.997
TENENTE ALBERTI?

38:21.265 --> 38:23.668
HE WILL BE
OUR CHAPERON.

38:34.912 --> 38:36.414
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

38:36.414 --> 38:38.916
LOOK AT HIM.

38:38.916 --> 38:41.085
HE'S GOOD-LOOKING.
HE'S ITALIAN.

38:41.085 --> 38:43.087
HE'S A DOCTOR.

38:43.087 --> 38:45.790
IT'S ALL OVER
FOR US.

38:45.790 --> 38:47.792
IT'LL NEVER WORK.

38:47.792 --> 38:50.294
TAKE ANOTHER LOOK.
HE'S ANCIENT.

38:50.294 --> 38:52.296
HE'S GOT TO BE
CLOSE TO 40.

38:52.296 --> 38:53.764
MAYBE MORE.

38:53.764 --> 38:57.101
NO WONDER HE WANTED
TO CHOP OFF MY LEG.

38:57.101 --> 38:59.370
HE MIGHT NOT
HAVE STOPPED THERE.

39:07.845 --> 39:09.780
Caracciolo: VON KUROWSKY?

39:09.780 --> 39:12.850
MY FATHER'S VERY
PROUD OF THAT "VON."

39:12.850 --> 39:15.186
HE'S FROM
KONIGSBERG, GERMANY.

39:15.186 --> 39:18.189
SO YOU ARE...
COME SI DICE?

39:18.189 --> 39:19.523
FIRST GENERATION?

39:19.523 --> 39:22.526
ON MY FATHER'S SIDE.
MY MOTHER'S AMERICAN.

39:22.526 --> 39:25.863
AND NOW YOU ARE NURSING
YOUNG AMERICANS IN ITALY,

39:25.863 --> 39:29.333
WHERE AUSTRIANS
AND GERMANS ARE...

39:29.333 --> 39:31.836
FIGHTING AGAINST US.

39:31.836 --> 39:34.372
THE RED CROSS
DOESN'T TAKE SIDES.

39:34.372 --> 39:38.209
THAT'S ONE OF
THE REASONS I JOINED.

39:38.209 --> 39:41.812
AND, UH, THE OTHERS?

39:41.812 --> 39:46.317
SOMEONE ELSE
ASKED ME THAT
JUST YESTERDAY.

39:46.317 --> 39:48.419
I HOPED TO BE
ASSIGNED TO ONE OF
THE SURGICAL TEAMS

39:48.419 --> 39:50.354
OPERATING ON THE FRONT.

39:50.354 --> 39:52.156
ME, TOO.

39:52.156 --> 39:53.924
SORRY, HARRY.

39:57.528 --> 39:59.296
THANK YOU.

40:03.834 --> 40:05.403
THANKS, PARTNER.

40:13.677 --> 40:15.179
WHAT'S HER NAME?

40:15.179 --> 40:16.847
Harry: EMILIA.

40:16.847 --> 40:19.517
EMILIA, SCUSI, SCUSI.

40:19.517 --> 40:22.853
UH, PER FAVORE,

40:22.853 --> 40:26.991
UH, CAN YOU GET US
SOME--SOME ALCOHOL?
SOME BRANDY?

40:26.991 --> 40:28.993
SOME BRAN-BRANDY?
BRANDY?

40:28.993 --> 40:30.194
ACQUA?

40:30.194 --> 40:32.196
NO, NO, NO,
BRANDY, BRANDY.

40:32.196 --> 40:33.831
THE--YOU KNOW,
IN A BOTTLE?

40:33.831 --> 40:35.166
AH, LATTE.

40:35.166 --> 40:36.667
NO, NO, NO, BRANDY.

40:36.667 --> 40:38.669
COME ON, BRANDY.

40:38.669 --> 40:40.004
AH...

40:40.004 --> 40:42.339
YES, BRANDY.

40:42.339 --> 40:47.478
NO. MI DISPIACE
MA NON á POSSIBILE.

40:47.478 --> 40:50.581
EMILIA. OH, EMILIA,
EMILIA, EMILIA.

40:50.581 --> 40:52.583
NO, EMILIA?
SCUSI, SCUSI, SCUSI.

40:52.583 --> 40:54.852
SEE, EMILIA,

40:54.852 --> 40:56.520
MY LEG...

40:56.520 --> 40:59.023
IT'S VERY SICK,
MY LEG.

40:59.023 --> 41:00.925
VERY SICK.
YOU NEED TO HELP ME.

41:00.925 --> 41:02.827
'CAUSE MY MOM
ISN'T HERE, SEE?

41:02.827 --> 41:04.995
AND--AND YOU NEED
TO BE MY MAMA.

41:06.263 --> 41:08.065
MAMA. MAMA, HUH?

41:08.065 --> 41:09.366
NO.

41:11.402 --> 41:12.736
VERY SORE.

41:12.736 --> 41:14.672
IT'S VERY SORE.

41:17.408 --> 41:19.076
VA BENE.

41:19.076 --> 41:22.179
VA BENE. VA BENE.
GRAZIE.

41:24.682 --> 41:26.984
GRAZIE, EMILIA.

41:29.920 --> 41:35.493
GOT HER.

41:35.493 --> 41:37.928
EMILIA.

41:37.928 --> 41:40.064
I THINK
SHE LIKES ME.

41:40.064 --> 41:41.499
HA HA HA HA.

41:41.499 --> 41:44.802
AH, COME ON, HARRY.
YOU KNOW WHAT THEY SAY
ABOUT NURSES.

41:44.802 --> 41:47.671
WHY--WHY DON'T YOU
JUST SHUT UP,
YOU BUNCH OF DRUNKS?

41:47.671 --> 41:49.673
THEY'RE ALWAYS
SEEING US NAKED,

41:49.673 --> 41:51.909
WASHING
OUR PRIVATE
PARTS FOR US.

41:51.909 --> 41:53.410
IT'S BOUND
TO AFFECT THEM.

41:53.410 --> 41:55.145
ESPECIALLY
MY PRIVATE PART.

41:55.145 --> 41:56.747
YOU'RE WAY OUT
OF LINE, KENYON.

41:56.747 --> 41:59.283
I--I DON'T KNOW
IF IT AFFECTS THEM,

41:59.283 --> 42:01.852
BUT WHEN I
FIRST GOT HERE,

42:01.852 --> 42:05.489
UM, ONE OF THEM,
OF COURSE I DON'T
KNOW WHICH ONE--

42:05.489 --> 42:07.291
IS THERE ANYBODY
DRINKING HERE?

42:07.291 --> 42:08.692
HERE.

42:08.692 --> 42:10.327
ANYWAY,

42:10.327 --> 42:13.464
SHE WAS DOWN THERE,
UM, SUDSING ME UP,

42:13.464 --> 42:16.934
AND IT WAS PRETTY
DAMN EMBARRASSING.

42:16.934 --> 42:20.104
ALL OUR NURSES SEEM
LIKE NICE GIRLS TO ME.

42:20.104 --> 42:21.972
EXCEPT MAYBE ROSIE.

42:21.972 --> 42:23.474
Larkin: THANK GOD.

42:23.474 --> 42:24.909
[LAUGHTER]

42:24.909 --> 42:26.410
Larkin:
WHOSE BET IS IT?

42:26.410 --> 42:29.079
WELL, GENTLEMEN,
HAVE WE ALL MOVED
OUR BOWELS TODAY?

42:29.079 --> 42:30.481
MR. LARKIN?

42:30.481 --> 42:31.982
8:32, MA'AM.

42:31.982 --> 42:34.118
GOOD. MMM?

42:34.118 --> 42:36.120
8:33, MA'AM.

42:36.120 --> 42:37.454
MM-HMM.

42:38.856 --> 42:40.224
8:34,
MA'AM.

42:44.495 --> 42:45.996
NOW THAT WE'RE
ALL SO REGULAR,

42:45.996 --> 42:47.464
DO YOU THINK WE COULD
HAVE OUR COCKTAILS TONIGHT

42:47.464 --> 42:49.133
WITHOUT THE USUAL GLOB
AT THE BOTTOM?

42:49.133 --> 42:53.203
THERE WILL
BE NO COCKTAILS
THIS EVENING, GENTLEMEN.

42:53.203 --> 42:54.939
PERIOD.

42:58.309 --> 43:00.110
IT WORKED.

43:00.110 --> 43:02.947
PLAYING CARDS,
GENTLEMEN, OR WHAT?

43:02.947 --> 43:05.182
RAISE YOU 2 BITS,
GENTLEMEN.

43:06.550 --> 43:08.052
CALL.

43:08.052 --> 43:11.388
JIMMY CALLS.
IT'S BIG TROUBLE.

43:11.388 --> 43:12.556
I FOLD.

43:13.624 --> 43:14.825
ERNIE...

43:14.825 --> 43:16.427
REMEMBER WHAT I SAID...

43:17.361 --> 43:18.829
BACK AT THE CANTEEN?

43:20.297 --> 43:24.435
I ALWAYS PLAY THE CARDS
I'M DEALT.

43:24.435 --> 43:25.502
Larkin: WHAT ARE YOU
DOING, VILLARD?

43:25.502 --> 43:26.570
THINKING.

43:28.072 --> 43:29.473
I DON'T...

43:30.407 --> 43:32.009
THINK I CAN...

43:33.043 --> 43:34.612
PLAY THIS HAND.

43:37.448 --> 43:38.682
SURE, YOU CAN.

43:41.819 --> 43:42.886
THREE 4s.

43:44.455 --> 43:46.357
THREE 9s.

43:46.357 --> 43:47.358
ERNIE?

43:47.358 --> 43:48.826
Larkin: ERNIE?

43:50.861 --> 43:51.929
I FOLDED.

43:53.030 --> 43:55.699
THAT'S, UH,
2 BUCKS TO ME, THEN.

43:55.699 --> 43:58.335
WAIT A MINUTE, WAIT.
McBRIDE CALLED.

44:01.372 --> 44:03.874
STRAIGHT, QUEEN HIGH.

44:03.874 --> 44:05.542
DON'T TRUST YOU, HEM.

44:05.542 --> 44:07.911
YOU TRUST ME,
DON'T YOU, JOSEPH?

44:12.116 --> 44:13.617
MMM...

44:13.617 --> 44:16.286
STRAIGHT,
QUEEN OF HEARTS HIGH.

44:18.889 --> 44:22.993
ALL RIGHT, BOYS,
WHY DON'T WE LET JIMMY
GET SOME REST?

44:32.369 --> 44:34.438
Mac: YEAH,
THAT'S BETTER.

44:34.438 --> 44:36.140
NOT SO FAST.

44:36.140 --> 44:39.109
GOOD.

44:40.377 --> 44:41.812
TIME FOR LUNCH, MAC.

44:41.812 --> 44:43.013
I'LL TAKE OVER.

44:43.013 --> 44:44.081
THANKS.

44:53.157 --> 44:55.559
Mac: HEY, KID,
TAKE IT EASY.
IT'S NOT A RACE.

44:55.559 --> 44:57.761
WHY DOES EVERYBODY
KEEP CALLING ME KID?

44:57.761 --> 44:59.096
WHY, INDEED?

45:01.465 --> 45:02.966
I'LL BE BACK
IN A HALF AN HOUR.

45:02.966 --> 45:04.268
ALL RIGHT.

45:06.303 --> 45:08.605
WELL, LOOK AT YOU.

45:08.605 --> 45:10.174
HOW WE DOING?

45:10.174 --> 45:11.475
PRETTY GOOD.

45:15.312 --> 45:16.680
VERY IMPRESSIVE.

45:17.848 --> 45:18.949
LET ME TRY WITH ONE.

45:18.949 --> 45:20.517
BY ALL MEANS.

45:23.454 --> 45:25.155
WHOA, EASY.

45:27.991 --> 45:29.827
YOU HAVE NO PATIENCE.

45:32.930 --> 45:34.231
SLOWLY.

45:40.270 --> 45:41.438
SEE?

45:43.140 --> 45:45.309
WHO'S THAT FELLA
IN NEW YORK,

45:45.309 --> 45:47.878
KEEPS WRITING YOU
ALL THOSE LETTERS?

45:49.179 --> 45:50.347
IT'S THIS WAY.

45:50.347 --> 45:51.648
WELL, HE'S...

45:52.616 --> 45:54.017
NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

45:55.719 --> 45:57.321
WHAT ABOUT CARACCIOLO?

45:58.756 --> 46:01.158
YOU GOT TO BE CAREFUL
ABOUT HIM.

46:01.158 --> 46:04.895
YOU KNOW,
HE'S OLD ENOUGH
TO BE YOUR FATHER.

46:04.895 --> 46:06.096
AHEM.

46:06.096 --> 46:08.732
HE'S ALSO NONE
OF YOUR BUSINESS.

46:08.732 --> 46:10.234
ALL RIGHT...

46:10.234 --> 46:12.569
BUT I MEANT EVERYTHING
I SAID THE OTHER NIGHT.

46:12.569 --> 46:14.438
LET'S TURN AROUND.

46:14.438 --> 46:16.106
SLOWLY.

46:16.106 --> 46:17.341
KID, YOU SAY
A LOT OF THINGS.

46:17.341 --> 46:20.444
I HAVE TROUBLE
KEEPING TRACK
OF ALL OF THEM.

46:20.444 --> 46:22.312
ABOUT YOU BEING
IN LOVE WITH ME.

46:22.312 --> 46:24.381
OH.

46:24.381 --> 46:26.250
ONLY NOT KNOWING IT.

46:26.250 --> 46:27.351
RIGHT.

46:28.652 --> 46:31.755
WELL, WHAT ABOUT YOU?

46:31.755 --> 46:35.359
I MEAN, I WOULD REALLY
HATE TO BE THE ONLY ONE
IN LOVE HERE.

46:35.359 --> 46:37.361
OH, I LOVE YOU
ALL RIGHT.

46:37.361 --> 46:42.733
NOBODY WILL EVER
LOVE ANYBODY AS MUCH
AS I LOVE YOU.

46:42.733 --> 46:44.001
ERNEST...

46:55.579 --> 46:57.981
Agnes:
JUST A LITTLE BIT. JUST...

46:57.981 --> 47:00.117
[PATIENT COUGHING]

47:02.186 --> 47:03.620
COME ON.

47:03.620 --> 47:05.589
JUST A LITTLE BIT.

47:05.589 --> 47:08.659
JUST A LITTLE BIT.
HERE YOU GO.

47:12.029 --> 47:14.064
JIMMY, PLEASE.

47:14.064 --> 47:16.867
JUST A LITTLE BIT.
YOU HAVE TO EAT
SOMETHING.

47:16.867 --> 47:19.937
IF YOU DON'T, JIMMY,
YOU WON'T MAKE IT.

47:21.839 --> 47:22.873
PLEASE.

47:22.873 --> 47:24.041
Burnside: UH,
ATTA BOY, ERNIE.

47:24.041 --> 47:25.976
JUST, UH--
LET ME JUST, UH--

47:25.976 --> 47:28.545
THERE. NOW, REMEMBER
TO SAY CHEESE.

47:29.413 --> 47:31.148
THERE YOU GO.

47:31.148 --> 47:33.717
"I GIVE
THIS SILVER MEDAL..."

47:35.085 --> 47:37.321
"FOR YOUR COURAGE ACTION

47:37.321 --> 47:39.089
"ON THE PIAVE RIVER

47:39.089 --> 47:41.692
ON THE 8th DAY
OF JULY..."

47:42.860 --> 47:44.027
"1918.

47:44.027 --> 47:47.231
"WHEN YOU ARE MUCH WOUNDED,

47:47.231 --> 47:48.232
"YOU...

47:48.232 --> 47:50.100
"ERNEST HEMINGWAY,

47:50.100 --> 47:52.936
"CARRIED PRIVATE
ROBERTO ZARDINI,

47:52.936 --> 47:55.639
"ALSO MUCH WOUNDED,

47:55.639 --> 47:57.241
BEHIND THE LINES..."

47:58.275 --> 48:01.879
"AND YOU DO NOT ACCEPT
MEDICAL ATTENTION

48:01.879 --> 48:05.449
UNTIL PRIVATE ZARDINI
IS ATTENDED TO FIRST."

48:14.558 --> 48:17.160
UH, YES, NOW,
FOR THIS, COULD WE--

48:17.160 --> 48:18.962
UH, ERNIE, COULD YOU JUST
COME UP HERE A BIT,

48:18.962 --> 48:21.064
AND, YOU...JUST TURN.

48:21.064 --> 48:22.299
AH, YES, UH, GOOD, GOOD.

48:22.299 --> 48:23.400
WE'LL--WE'LL DO THAT
IN JUST A MINUTE.

48:23.400 --> 48:25.369
LET'S JUST
GET THIS FIRST,

48:25.369 --> 48:27.004
AND, UH--
YES, IN CLOSER.

48:27.004 --> 48:29.940
GOOD, YES.
AH, LET'S GET ONE WITH
ALL THE YOUNG GENTLEMEN.

48:29.940 --> 48:31.775
NOW, JUST OVER AGAINST
THIS WALL. IF WE--

48:31.775 --> 48:33.610
ERNIE, WILL YOU JUST, UH--

48:33.610 --> 48:34.611
OVER HERE IN THE CENTER.

48:34.611 --> 48:35.913
AND, YES, UH, NURSE,

48:35.913 --> 48:38.081
COULD YOU JOIN HIM,
PLEASE? RIGHT HERE.

48:38.081 --> 48:39.983
THAT--THAT'S FINE.
IF YOU'D RATHER
BE THERE, THAT'S OK.

48:39.983 --> 48:41.718
AND OUR--PLEASE.

48:41.718 --> 48:42.719
AND CAN WE SEE HEADS
THROUGH THERE?

48:42.719 --> 48:43.954
STAND UP IN THE BACK
THERE, GENTLEMEN.

48:43.954 --> 48:45.555
THERE YOU GO.

48:49.426 --> 48:51.194
I SUPPOSE
CONGRATULATIONS
ARE IN ORDER.

48:51.194 --> 48:52.329
THANKS.

48:57.200 --> 48:59.069
Caracciolo:
YOUR AMERICAN TROOPS

48:59.069 --> 49:01.438
ARE TO JOIN US SOON...

49:01.438 --> 49:04.508
AND THERE WILL BE
A BIG PUSH.

49:07.778 --> 49:09.880
AND I MUST LEAVE
TOMORROW

49:09.880 --> 49:13.016
TO SET UP A FORWARD
SURGICAL UNIT.

49:16.219 --> 49:18.388
I WAS HOPING...

49:18.388 --> 49:22.192
WE COULD HAVE ANOTHER DRIVE
TOGETHER BEFORE I GO.

49:23.927 --> 49:26.863
I'M SORRY. I PROMISED
TWO OF THE PATIENTS

49:26.863 --> 49:30.167
THAT I WOULD TAKE THEM
ON A SMALL EXCURSION.

49:31.401 --> 49:33.170
YOUNG HEMINGWAY?

49:35.806 --> 49:38.175
MAYBE SOME OTHER TIME.

49:39.943 --> 49:41.511
I WOULD LIKE THAT.

49:44.715 --> 49:46.783
[COUNTING QUIETLY]

49:55.892 --> 49:57.961
CAN I TALK TO YOU?

49:59.296 --> 50:00.397
UHH.

50:00.397 --> 50:02.366
I'VE LOST COUNT.

50:02.366 --> 50:04.701
IT'S HARRY.
I'M WORRIED ABOUT HIM.

50:04.701 --> 50:06.703
WHAT IS IT?

50:06.703 --> 50:09.973
HE'S A LOT SICKER
THAN HE'S LETTING ON.

50:09.973 --> 50:11.174
OH, HE IS, IS HE?

50:11.174 --> 50:12.175
YEAH.

50:12.175 --> 50:14.311
1, 2, 3, 4...

50:14.311 --> 50:16.813
IN FACT, I DON'T THINK
ANYBODY REALIZES JUST...

50:17.781 --> 50:20.517
HOW SICK THE POOR FELLOW
REALLY IS.

50:20.517 --> 50:22.386
AND YOU DO?

50:22.386 --> 50:23.954
MMM.

50:27.691 --> 50:29.926
E-ERNIE, DON'T--

50:29.926 --> 50:31.361
PLEASE DON'T DO THAT.

50:31.361 --> 50:36.500
SORRY.
I JUST WANTED TO SEE
WHAT IT WAS MADE OF.

50:36.500 --> 50:39.069
IS IT SOME KIND
OF COTTON?

50:40.203 --> 50:42.406
IT'S A CHAMBRAY.

50:44.074 --> 50:45.842
IT MUST GET WARM
IN THE HEAT.

50:45.842 --> 50:47.577
IT DOES.

50:49.046 --> 50:50.147
1, 2...

50:50.147 --> 50:53.150
THE THING I WAS
THINKING IS THAT...

50:53.150 --> 50:54.518
IT MIGHT NOT BE
SUCH A GOOD IDEA

50:54.518 --> 50:58.088
FOR HIM TO COME
ON THE PICNIC WITH US.

50:59.589 --> 51:01.191
ERNIE, PLEASE.

51:03.427 --> 51:05.195
WHAT ARE THESE, SILK?

51:06.163 --> 51:08.331
COTTON--COTTON.

51:08.331 --> 51:09.399
AHEM.

51:10.934 --> 51:13.603
ANYWAYS, I WAS--I WAS
THINKING THAT IF HARRY
STAYED HERE...

51:14.604 --> 51:17.841
AND WE WENT ON
WITHOUT HIM, THAT...

51:17.841 --> 51:19.142
HE MIGHT BE DISAPPOINTED
FOR A WHILE,

51:19.142 --> 51:21.211
BUT, I THINK,
IN THE END,

51:21.211 --> 51:22.712
IT'D BE BEST.

51:22.712 --> 51:26.316
YOU DO HAVE
HIS BEST INTERESTS
AT HEART.

51:28.618 --> 51:30.654
BELIEVE ME, I DO.

51:38.462 --> 51:41.031
SHALL I TELL HIM,
OR WILL YOU?

51:41.031 --> 51:43.166
OH, I--I THINK...

51:43.166 --> 51:46.937
MAYBE YOU SHOULD--
YOU SHOULD LEAVE THAT
UP TO ME.

52:03.453 --> 52:06.423
WHAT'S THE MATTER, ERNIE?
CAT GOT YOUR TONGUE?

52:13.830 --> 52:15.432
ANDIAMO.

52:15.432 --> 52:16.500
Driver: SU.

52:18.101 --> 52:19.569
Teresa: FERMO!

52:19.569 --> 52:21.138
FERMO, PER FAVORE!

52:25.175 --> 52:26.910
E' MIO ZIO.

52:26.910 --> 52:28.178
QUESTO E MIO ZIO,

52:28.178 --> 52:30.580
IL PADRE DI
ROBERTO ZARDINI.

52:30.580 --> 52:32.449
VORREBBE DARE
AL SIGNOR ERNIE

52:32.449 --> 52:34.284
LA MANTELLA
DI SUO FIGLIO.

52:34.284 --> 52:37.821
ERNIE, IT'S
ROBERTO ZARDINI'S FATHER,

52:37.821 --> 52:41.057
AND--AND THAT IS
ROBERTO'S CAPE.

52:42.025 --> 52:43.026
MIA MOGLIE ED IO--

52:43.026 --> 52:45.228
HE WANTS ME TO HAVE IT?
MM-HMM.

52:45.228 --> 52:48.899
MIA MOGLIE ED IO LA
RINGRAZIAMO PER QUELLO
CHE HA FATTO.

52:48.899 --> 52:50.967
THANK YOU,
SIGNOR ZARDINI.

52:50.967 --> 52:52.135
GRAZIE.

52:58.742 --> 53:01.178
PLEASE ASK HER IF...

53:01.178 --> 53:02.412
UH--UH...

53:02.412 --> 53:04.381
ROBERTO...

53:04.381 --> 53:05.549
LUI...

53:06.783 --> 53:07.984
E' MORTO.

53:12.389 --> 53:13.390
DI--

53:13.390 --> 53:15.625
DI A TUO...

53:15.625 --> 53:16.726
UH...

53:16.726 --> 53:19.196
YOUR UNCLE THAT...

53:19.196 --> 53:21.131
SIGNOR ERNIE á, UM,

53:21.131 --> 53:22.265
MOLTO...

53:23.667 --> 53:24.668
Ernest: GRAZIE.

53:24.668 --> 53:26.036
H-HONORED...

53:26.036 --> 53:27.504
DI--DI RICEVERE...

53:27.504 --> 53:28.838
UH...

53:28.838 --> 53:29.940
LA MANTELLA...

53:29.940 --> 53:32.342
DI SUO FIGLIO.

53:33.276 --> 53:35.278
E' MOLTO ONORATO.

53:35.278 --> 53:36.446
GRAZIE.

53:57.300 --> 53:59.336
THERE'S A HUNDRED TINY
LITTLE FISH DOWN HERE

53:59.336 --> 54:01.071
NIBBLING ON MY LEGS.

54:01.071 --> 54:02.839
LUCKY BASTARDS.

54:04.774 --> 54:06.576
IF THIS WAS
WALLOON LAKE,
THEY'D BE BASS,

54:06.576 --> 54:08.478
AND I'D HAVE REELED IN
6 OF THEM BY NOW.

54:08.478 --> 54:10.013
Agnes: WALLOON?

54:10.013 --> 54:12.415
IT'S IN MICHIGAN.

54:12.415 --> 54:14.451
SOMEDAY,
I'LL TAKE YOU THERE.

54:14.451 --> 54:16.820
I'LL CATCH 'EM.
YOU'LL CLEAN 'EM.

54:16.820 --> 54:18.421
WE'LL BOTH EAT 'EM.

54:18.421 --> 54:20.257
THE DAY I CLEAN A BASS
WILL BE THE DAY

54:20.257 --> 54:21.558
A ONE-LEGGED,
BIG-HEADED BOY

54:21.558 --> 54:24.027
SWIMS HIMSELF
ACROSS THIS LAKE.

54:24.027 --> 54:25.695
RIGHT.

54:25.695 --> 54:27.197
Harry: ERNIE.
ERNIE.

54:27.197 --> 54:28.765
ERNIE!
ERNIE!

54:28.765 --> 54:29.899
ERNEST.

54:29.899 --> 54:30.967
ERNIE.

54:36.573 --> 54:37.574
ERNIE!

54:37.574 --> 54:38.842
CAN YOU SWIM?

54:38.842 --> 54:40.810
I HOPE NOT.

54:41.745 --> 54:43.079
ERNIE, YOU--

54:43.079 --> 54:44.080
[ERNEST GASPING
FOR BREATH]

54:44.080 --> 54:45.348
COME ON, ERNIE--
OK, FINE!

54:45.348 --> 54:47.684
I'LL CLEAN--I'LL CLEAN--
I'LL CLEAN ONE FISH.

54:48.785 --> 54:49.786
ERNIE?

54:49.786 --> 54:51.588
TWO!?

54:51.588 --> 54:53.356
FINE, ERNIE.
OK, YOU WIN, ERNIE.

54:53.356 --> 54:56.059
I'LL CLEAN
ALL 6 STUPID FISH.

54:58.094 --> 54:59.229
HOW MANY?

54:59.229 --> 55:00.230
WHAT?

55:00.230 --> 55:01.298
HOW MANY?

55:01.298 --> 55:03.566
6...

55:03.566 --> 55:04.634
FISH.

55:06.303 --> 55:07.570
ALL RIGHT.

55:15.245 --> 55:17.314
[ERNEST AND AGNES LAUGH]

55:18.748 --> 55:22.619
"I HAVE A RENDEZVOUS
WITH DEATH AT SOME
DISPUTED BARRICADE.

55:22.619 --> 55:24.654
WHEN SPRING COMES BACK
WITH RUSTLING--"

55:24.654 --> 55:26.823
ET CETERA, ET CETERA,
AD NAUSEAM.

55:26.823 --> 55:28.825
"I SHALL NOT FAIL
THAT RENDEZVOUS."

55:28.825 --> 55:30.393
FOR GOD'S SAKES,
ERNIE, EVERY--

55:30.393 --> 55:33.063
EVERY FRESHMAN AT HARVARD
HAS THAT ONE MEMORIZED.

55:33.063 --> 55:35.165
I CAN'T IMAGINE
WHAT'S STICKING
IN YOUR CRAW.

55:35.165 --> 55:38.168
COME ON, YOU TWO.
YOU'RE BOTH GETTING
ON MY NERVES.

55:38.168 --> 55:40.136
Harry: NOW, ARE YOU
GOING TO PRANCE AROUND
ALL AFTERNOON

55:40.136 --> 55:44.641
IN A DEAD MAN'S CAPE
LIKE SOME THIRD-RATE
SHAKESPEAREAN ACTOR?

55:44.641 --> 55:46.209
PARDON ME, OLD MAN,
BUT I CARRIED HIM

55:46.209 --> 55:48.712
ACROSS THE DAMN
BATTLEFIELD ON MY BACK.

55:48.712 --> 55:51.014
AND EVERY TIME YOU
TELL THE STORY, IT GETS
BIGGER AND BIGGER.

55:51.014 --> 55:52.716
FIRST, IT WAS
20 YARDS, AND THEN 50,

55:52.716 --> 55:53.817
AND NOW IT'S
THE WHOLE BATTLEFIELD?

55:53.817 --> 55:55.919
I'M LEAVING
IF THIS DOES NOT STOP.

55:55.919 --> 55:59.289
TOO BAD, HARRY. IT MUST
HAVE BEEN TOUGH FOR YOU
THESE LAST FEW WEEKS.

55:59.289 --> 56:01.124
THE REST OF US SHOT UP
OR, AT LEAST, INJURED,

56:01.124 --> 56:04.294
AND YOU IN THE HOSPITAL
BECAUSE YOU TURNED YELLOW.

56:04.294 --> 56:06.796
ERNIE, THAT WAS A STUPID
AND THOUGHTLESS
THING TO SAY.

56:06.796 --> 56:08.598
WHOSE SIDE ARE YOU ON,
ANYWAY?

56:08.598 --> 56:11.701
WHOEVER WILL PUT AN END
TO THIS RIDICULOUS
ARGUMENT.

56:11.701 --> 56:14.771
I WILL, AGNES,
BUT JUST FOR YOU.

56:20.744 --> 56:23.079
ARE YOU GOING TO RIDE BACK
WITH US PEACEFULLY?

56:23.079 --> 56:24.547
I'D RATHER WALK.

56:24.547 --> 56:27.217
WALK, THEN.
COME ON, HARRY.

56:27.217 --> 56:28.952
WELL, ERNIE, IT LOOKS
AS THOUGH THE BEST MAN

56:28.952 --> 56:31.454
HAS BEEN GRANTED
THE LADY'S FAVOR AFTER ALL.

56:31.454 --> 56:32.555
OH, YOU'RE RIGHT, HARRY,

56:32.555 --> 56:34.090
AND IT WAS GRANTED TO ME
THE OTHER NIGHT...

56:34.090 --> 56:36.025
IN HER BED.

57:13.363 --> 57:15.532
ALL RIGHT, GIRLS,
LIFT IT UP.

57:24.908 --> 57:28.578
De Long: WE'RE
TRYING TO GET IT
STRAIGHT, ROSIE.

57:28.578 --> 57:30.880
Man:
CONGRATULATE, ERNIE!

57:30.880 --> 57:32.615
CONGRATULATE, ERNIE!

57:37.987 --> 57:39.989
[DISTANT ARTILLERY FIRE]

57:39.989 --> 57:41.991
Caracciolo: WE HAVE
TO KEEP...QUIET.

57:41.991 --> 57:42.992
American surgeon:
HE'S GOOD.

57:42.992 --> 57:46.396
AND, UH, I'LL COME BACK--
WHO KNOWS...

57:47.897 --> 57:51.000
Agnes, quietly:
I THINK SO.

57:51.000 --> 57:54.370
[HOARSELY]
I HOPE...

57:54.370 --> 57:57.207
I--I CAN'T HEAR YOU.

57:57.207 --> 57:58.441
I HOPE...

57:58.441 --> 58:01.144
I HOPE? I HOPE...

58:01.144 --> 58:03.813
EVERYONE...

58:03.813 --> 58:05.882
IS...

58:08.184 --> 58:10.854
ALL RIGHT...

58:11.988 --> 58:12.989
THERE.

58:12.989 --> 58:14.791
THERE? THERE.

58:14.791 --> 58:17.427
[DISTANT KLAXON HORN]

58:17.427 --> 58:20.263
JIMMY, I'M TERRIBLY
SORRY. THE OTHER--

58:20.263 --> 58:21.998
I'M AFRAID THE OTHER
PATIENTS HAVE ARRIVED,

58:21.998 --> 58:25.068
SO I'M GOING
TO HAVE TO LEAVE.

58:26.936 --> 58:28.471
Jimmy: YOU...

58:28.471 --> 58:29.739
WILL...

58:29.739 --> 58:31.007
SEND IT...

58:33.710 --> 58:34.811
WON'T YOU?

58:34.811 --> 58:39.282
I PROMISE. I'LL BE BACK
AS SOON AS I CAN.

58:39.282 --> 58:41.684
WE'RE GETTING MORE
THAN WE THOUGHT.
GO GET THE DOCTOR.

58:41.684 --> 58:43.353
WE'LL BE USING
ALL THE BEDS.

58:43.353 --> 58:44.621
WE NEED WHEELCHAIRS.

58:44.621 --> 58:46.689
Nurse: YES,
MISS DE LONG.

58:48.291 --> 58:49.292
LISTEN, I NEED TO TALK.

58:49.292 --> 58:50.927
KID, THIS IS
NOT THE TIME.

58:50.927 --> 58:52.996
I'VE BEEN SUCH AN IDIOT.

58:52.996 --> 58:55.465
IT'S OVER, ISN'T IT,
YOU AND ME?

58:55.465 --> 58:58.635
I MADE A MESS OUT OF IT,
AND NOW YOU'RE NEVER
GOING TO FORGIVE ME.

59:08.444 --> 59:12.115
LET'S MOVE THE PATIENTS
INTO BED CAREFULLY
BUT QUICKLY, EVERYONE,

59:12.115 --> 59:13.550
AND GET THESE STRETCHERS
OUT OF HERE.

59:13.550 --> 59:14.551
Burton: NURSE?

59:14.551 --> 59:16.653
ALL RIGHT, SON.

59:16.653 --> 59:17.720
WHAT IS IT, BURTON?

59:17.720 --> 59:18.721
BATHROOM.

59:18.721 --> 59:19.722
I'LL TAKE YOU.

59:19.722 --> 59:21.457
De Long: PUT THE AMPUTEE
IN BED 22.

59:21.457 --> 59:24.093
I WANT THE DOCTOR
TO SEE HIM FIRST.

59:24.093 --> 59:25.662
AND THE HEAD WOUND
IN 20--

59:25.662 --> 59:28.264
BE SURE TO KEEP HIM
COVERED...

59:48.151 --> 59:50.153
[BOTTLES CLATTER]

01:00:07.637 --> 01:00:10.006
OH, DIO SANTO.

01:00:13.309 --> 01:00:14.577
AIUTO!

01:00:14.577 --> 01:00:16.479
AIUTO, A MORTO!

01:00:17.447 --> 01:00:18.648
DEAD!

01:00:18.648 --> 01:00:20.116
JIMMY DEAD!

01:00:45.174 --> 01:00:46.909
Agnes: KID, GO AWAY.

01:00:58.154 --> 01:00:59.222
WHAT'S THAT?

01:01:01.090 --> 01:01:04.160
IT'S THE LETTER THAT
JIMMY WAS DICTATING.

01:01:08.431 --> 01:01:10.967
"DEAR MOM AND DAD,

01:01:10.967 --> 01:01:12.969
"THANKS FOR THE PACKAGE.

01:01:12.969 --> 01:01:14.737
"THE WEATHER HERE
IS HOT,

01:01:14.737 --> 01:01:17.507
"BUT MAYBE IT WILL
COOL DOWN SOON.

01:01:17.507 --> 01:01:19.242
"THE FOOD IS GOOD.

01:01:19.242 --> 01:01:21.911
"EVERYONE IS
ALL RIGHT HERE.

01:01:21.911 --> 01:01:25.782
I HOPE EVERYONE
IS ALL RIGHT THERE."

01:01:25.782 --> 01:01:29.852
I WAS TRYING TO THINK
OF HOW TO FINISH IT.

01:01:31.654 --> 01:01:32.722
ERNIE.

01:01:34.323 --> 01:01:35.892
DEAR MOM AND DAD--

01:01:36.959 --> 01:01:38.628
START OVER AGAIN.

01:01:43.099 --> 01:01:44.701
Ernest:
DEAR MOM AND DAD...

01:01:47.336 --> 01:01:50.406
THE THING THIS WAR
HAS TAUGHT ME...

01:01:51.774 --> 01:01:56.846
IS THAT IT'S IMPORTANT
TO GET THINGS SAID
BEFORE IT'S TOO LATE.

01:01:58.915 --> 01:01:59.982
FIRST...

01:02:02.985 --> 01:02:08.057
YOU'VE BEEN
THE VERY BEST PARENTS
A SON COULD EVER ASK FOR.

01:02:11.494 --> 01:02:13.563
WHEN I WAS A KID...

01:02:15.098 --> 01:02:19.135
AND I USED TO GET SCARED
OF THE DARK,

01:02:19.135 --> 01:02:21.771
IT WAS THE THOUGHT
THAT YOU WERE THERE

01:02:21.771 --> 01:02:23.840
THAT GOT ME THROUGH IT.

01:02:33.382 --> 01:02:35.985
I THINK ABOUT THAT
A LOT...

01:02:38.755 --> 01:02:41.324
BECAUSE I GUESS
I'M SCARED NOW.

01:02:46.863 --> 01:02:49.932
I DON'T KNOW
IF I CAN MAKE IT...

01:02:51.801 --> 01:02:52.702
AND IF I DON'T...

01:02:56.405 --> 01:02:58.808
PLEASE UNDERSTAND
THAT SOMETIMES...

01:03:04.614 --> 01:03:06.749
I HAVE TO GO
TO PLACES ALONE.

01:03:15.224 --> 01:03:16.793
BUT WHATEVER HAPPENS...

01:03:19.629 --> 01:03:21.230
ALWAYS KNOW THAT...

01:03:22.231 --> 01:03:25.201
I WILL BE
YOUR LOVING SON...

01:03:25.201 --> 01:03:26.702
JIMMY.

01:03:48.724 --> 01:03:50.293
I LOVE YOU.

01:04:20.957 --> 01:04:22.425
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

01:04:22.425 --> 01:04:24.994
Mac: AGGIE, GUMSHOE'S
ON HER ROUNDS.

01:05:16.212 --> 01:05:18.781
HARRY, WE'RE LEAVING.
AGNES IS LOOKING
FOR YOU.

01:05:18.781 --> 01:05:19.849
ALL RIGHT.

01:05:21.918 --> 01:05:23.119
HEY, HAVE YOU
SEEN ERNIE?

01:05:23.119 --> 01:05:24.186
NO.

01:05:25.288 --> 01:05:27.056
HARRY. HARRY.

01:05:27.056 --> 01:05:28.424
THANK--THANK GOD
I'VE FOUND YOU.

01:05:28.424 --> 01:05:30.526
THEY'RE MOVING
SOME OF US CLOSER
TO THE FRONT.

01:05:30.526 --> 01:05:32.595
I NEED FOR YOU
TO DO ME A HUGE FAVOR.

01:05:32.595 --> 01:05:33.729
ANYTHING.

01:05:33.729 --> 01:05:35.431
Mac: AG, COME ON.

01:05:35.431 --> 01:05:36.732
I'LL BE--I'LL BE
RIGHT THERE.

01:05:36.732 --> 01:05:39.101
I CAN'T FIND ERNIE
ANYWHERE, AND...

01:05:39.101 --> 01:05:42.171
COULD YOU GIVE THIS
TO HIM FOR ME?

01:05:51.814 --> 01:05:54.116
I'M SORRY, HARRY.
I--I...

01:05:54.116 --> 01:05:58.020
I HONESTLY NEVER
EXPECTED ANYTHING
LIKE THIS TO HAPPEN.

01:05:59.722 --> 01:06:01.590
AG, WE'RE LEAVING.

01:06:01.590 --> 01:06:03.993
YOU WON'T FORGET?

01:06:03.993 --> 01:06:05.895
I WON'T FORGET.

01:06:06.796 --> 01:06:07.863
BYE.

01:06:16.539 --> 01:06:17.840
Harry: ERNIE!

01:06:25.181 --> 01:06:27.316
LISTEN, OLD MAN,
I'M GLAD TO RUN INTO YOU
WITH NO ONE ELSE AROUND.

01:06:27.316 --> 01:06:30.820
THERE'S SOMETHING I'D LIKE
TO GET OFF MY CHEST.

01:06:30.820 --> 01:06:35.925
THAT BUSINESS
I SAID THE OTHER DAY
ABOUT AGNES AND ME WAS...

01:06:35.925 --> 01:06:37.493
WELL, IT WAS ALL BULL.

01:06:39.729 --> 01:06:40.730
YEAH.

01:06:40.730 --> 01:06:41.897
AHEM.

01:06:41.897 --> 01:06:42.965
WELL, UH...

01:06:44.066 --> 01:06:47.436
SHE--SHE ASKED ME
TO GIVE THIS TO YOU.

01:06:50.072 --> 01:06:53.542
ORDERS CAME THROUGH,
AND, UH...

01:06:53.542 --> 01:06:54.977
THEY SENT HER...

01:06:54.977 --> 01:06:57.046
[OPENS ENVELOPE]

01:07:02.485 --> 01:07:04.086
I'M SORRY, ERNIE.

01:07:05.087 --> 01:07:06.689
I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL.

01:07:24.607 --> 01:07:26.509
Agnes: DEAREST ERNIE,

01:07:26.509 --> 01:07:27.710
NEW ORDERS CAME THROUGH,

01:07:27.710 --> 01:07:32.281
AND, SUDDENLY, I FIND MYSELF
ON MY WAY TO THE FRONT.

01:07:33.482 --> 01:07:35.084
I'M WRITING THIS
WITH A SHAKY HAND,

01:07:35.084 --> 01:07:38.888
PARTLY BECAUSE
I AM AFRAID

01:07:38.888 --> 01:07:43.893
AND PARTLY BECAUSE IT IS
SO HARD TO SAY GOOD-BYE.

01:07:43.893 --> 01:07:47.530
I WANTED TO SAY THIS
TO YOU IN PERSON...

01:07:47.530 --> 01:07:49.598
[KLAXON HORNS HONKING]

01:07:55.571 --> 01:07:57.640
[BUGLE BLOWS REVEILLE]

01:08:08.017 --> 01:08:09.585
Agnes: I'M ON DUTY.

01:08:10.586 --> 01:08:12.154
JUST READ YOUR LETTER.

01:08:21.363 --> 01:08:23.099
Ernest: DEAREST AGGIE,

01:08:23.099 --> 01:08:27.403
I MISS AND YEARN TO SEE YOU
MORE THAN WORDS CAN SAY.

01:08:27.403 --> 01:08:30.773
EVERY TIME SOMEONE
COMES THROUGH THE DOOR,

01:08:30.773 --> 01:08:34.542
I CAN'T HELP BUT LOOK UP
AND HOPE IT'S YOU.

01:08:34.542 --> 01:08:35.810
I WEAR THE RING
YOU GAVE ME

01:08:35.810 --> 01:08:40.616
AND LOOK AT IT MAYBE
A HUNDRED TIMES A DAY.

01:08:40.616 --> 01:08:42.952
HARRY HAS NEW ORDERS
TO REPORT TO YOUR SECTOR,

01:08:42.952 --> 01:08:46.122
BUT THE RED CROSS MEDICS
TOOK ONE LOOK AT MY LEG

01:08:46.122 --> 01:08:48.524
AND TURNED ME DOWN.

01:08:48.524 --> 01:08:50.593
I MAY SURPRISE THEM YET.

01:08:51.760 --> 01:08:53.229
CALMA,
SEI IN BUONE MANI.

01:08:53.229 --> 01:08:54.430
Doctor: I NEED MORE ETHER!

01:08:54.430 --> 01:08:55.731
NURSE, HURRY!

01:08:59.768 --> 01:09:02.037
Second doctor: STOP WHAT
YOU'RE DOING AND WAIT.

01:09:02.037 --> 01:09:03.872
RIGHT, NURSE, ETHER.

01:09:05.608 --> 01:09:07.643
COMING THROUGH.
COMING THROUGH.

01:09:11.514 --> 01:09:12.715
HE'S COMING AROUND.

01:09:16.085 --> 01:09:17.653
Doctor: HOLD HIM DOWN!

01:09:18.953 --> 01:09:21.055
GET THOSE SWABS--
SISTER, QUICKLY!

01:09:22.323 --> 01:09:23.392
Doctor: HURRY!

01:09:31.734 --> 01:09:35.337
IF I HAD KNOWN
IT WAS GOING TO BE SO...

01:09:35.337 --> 01:09:37.540
I WOULDN'T HAVE ASKED THEM
TO ASSIGN YOU HERE.

01:09:37.540 --> 01:09:38.774
Doctor:
CUT FOR ME, PLEASE.

01:09:38.774 --> 01:09:41.911
THIS IS WHAT
I WAS TRAINED FOR.

01:09:41.911 --> 01:09:44.947
YOU HAVE BEEN UP
ALMOST 24 HOURS.

01:09:44.947 --> 01:09:45.948
SO HAVE YOU.

01:09:45.948 --> 01:09:47.149
Doctor: AND AGAIN.

01:09:54.356 --> 01:09:56.091
Man: I'VE GOT
TO GET IT!

01:10:29.124 --> 01:10:31.260
YOU ARE SUCH A CHILD.

01:10:33.662 --> 01:10:37.233
THIS WAS A STUPID
THING TO DO.

01:10:37.233 --> 01:10:39.568
WHEN ARE YOU GOING
TO GROW UP?

01:10:39.568 --> 01:10:41.704
I COULDN'T LEAVE
WITHOUT SEEING YOU AGAIN.

01:10:41.704 --> 01:10:43.205
LEAVE?

01:10:43.205 --> 01:10:45.040
I'M ON ORDERS
BACK TO THE STATES.

01:10:45.040 --> 01:10:46.308
WHEN?

01:10:46.308 --> 01:10:48.844
I GOT TO CATCH A TRAIN
TOMORROW MORNING AT 5:30.

01:10:48.844 --> 01:10:50.512
Mac: THEY'VE
CALLED US, AG.

01:10:50.512 --> 01:10:52.081
MM-HMM.

01:10:56.352 --> 01:10:58.654
I CAME TO TELL YOU
THAT I LOVE YOU.

01:11:00.856 --> 01:11:03.525
AND I WILL LOVE YOU
FOREVER.

01:11:08.464 --> 01:11:11.333
THERE'S A HOTEL
BY THE TRAIN STATION.

01:11:14.403 --> 01:11:18.140
KID, THAT'S NOT A HOTEL.
THAT'S A BROTHEL.

01:11:19.441 --> 01:11:21.777
THERE'S NOWHERE ELSE.
I'VE ASKED AROUND.

01:11:26.515 --> 01:11:28.517
WILL YOU...

01:11:38.260 --> 01:11:40.329
I'LL TRY.

01:12:55.637 --> 01:12:58.841
[PEOPLE LAUGHING]

01:12:58.841 --> 01:13:01.076
[ACCORDION PLAYS
ROMANTIC AIR]

01:13:21.764 --> 01:13:22.998
[HINGE CREAKS]

01:13:39.181 --> 01:13:43.018
I'M SORRY. I DIDN'T
THINK IT WAS GOING
TO BE THIS BAD.

01:13:43.018 --> 01:13:45.087
IT'S JUST...

01:13:45.087 --> 01:13:47.222
PART OF WAR.

01:13:47.222 --> 01:13:52.661
MEN DESPERATE FOR SEX,
WOMEN DESPERATE FOR...MONEY.

01:13:55.397 --> 01:13:58.734
YOU SHOULDN'T
BE HERE.

01:13:58.734 --> 01:14:00.969
LET'S GO SOMEWHERE
ELSE, ANYWHERE.

01:14:02.171 --> 01:14:04.106
[CLOSES DOOR]

01:14:18.086 --> 01:14:21.123
IT WASN'T SUPPOSED
TO BE LIKE THIS.

01:14:21.123 --> 01:14:23.025
NEVER MIND.

01:14:26.995 --> 01:14:30.399
WE WERE GOING TO BE
IN THE MOST BEAUTIFUL
PLACE ON GOD'S EARTH.

01:14:32.801 --> 01:14:35.070
THEN CLOSE YOUR EYES.

01:16:37.793 --> 01:16:41.196
I TOLD YOU I WASN'T
A VERY GOOD DANCER.

01:16:43.265 --> 01:16:47.135
TO ME, THIS IS
THE MOST BEAUTIFUL WALTZ
IN THE WORLD.

01:16:48.537 --> 01:16:50.839
THIS ISN'T A WALTZ.

01:16:50.839 --> 01:16:53.075
EVEN I KNOW THAT.

01:17:20.369 --> 01:17:21.703
YOU'LL WRITE ME,
RIGHT?

01:17:21.703 --> 01:17:23.572
I'LL WRITE YOU
EVERY DAY.

01:17:25.607 --> 01:17:26.708
BE CAREFUL.

01:17:26.708 --> 01:17:28.110
I WILL.

01:17:28.110 --> 01:17:29.878
[WHISTLE BLOWS]

01:17:30.912 --> 01:17:31.980
PROMISE?
YES.

01:17:31.980 --> 01:17:33.649
[TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING]

01:17:33.649 --> 01:17:36.018
I LOVE YOU,
MRS. KID.

01:17:36.018 --> 01:17:38.420
WHEN THIS IS OVER,
WE'LL GET MARRIED,
RIGHT?

01:17:38.420 --> 01:17:40.088
RIGHT.
MR. AND MRS. KID.

01:17:40.088 --> 01:17:42.991
TELL ME YOU LOVE ME.
I NEED TO HEAR YOU
SAY IT.

01:17:43.959 --> 01:17:45.193
TELL ME.

01:17:46.161 --> 01:17:48.230
[DROWNED OUT BY NOISE]
I LOVE YOU.

01:17:49.164 --> 01:17:51.133
SAY IT.

01:17:53.535 --> 01:17:56.338
[QUIETLY]
I LOVE YOU.

01:18:26.301 --> 01:18:29.304
WELL, THAT'S--
THAT'S TERRIFIC NEWS.

01:18:30.839 --> 01:18:34.409
MAYBE--MAYBE
HE AND I HAVE HAD
OUR DIFFERENCES,

01:18:34.409 --> 01:18:36.578
BUT HE'S ALL RIGHT.

01:18:38.747 --> 01:18:42.517
I HATE TO ADMIT IT,
BUT HE'S MORE
THAN ALL RIGHT.

01:18:43.485 --> 01:18:44.986
YOU'LL DO HIM
A WORLD OF GOOD.

01:18:46.288 --> 01:18:48.790
WHAT'S THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

01:18:48.790 --> 01:18:50.659
YOU KNOW ERNIE AND...

01:18:50.659 --> 01:18:53.061
HE NEEDS SOMEONE THAT
CAN TAKE CARE OF HIM.

01:18:53.061 --> 01:18:54.429
THAT'S HIS MOTHER'S JOB,
HARRY.

01:18:54.429 --> 01:18:56.732
I DON'T WANT
TO BE HIS MOTHER.

01:18:56.732 --> 01:19:00.368
EVEN THOUGH IT'LL PROBABLY
LOOK AS THOUGH I AM.

01:19:00.368 --> 01:19:02.771
NOW, WHAT'S AN
8-YEAR AGE DIFFERENCE
WHEN YOU'RE IN LOVE?

01:19:02.771 --> 01:19:05.073
7. HE JUST
HAD A BIRTHDAY.

01:19:05.073 --> 01:19:06.675
IS THIS ENOUGH?

01:19:07.709 --> 01:19:09.211
WELL, SO WHAT.

01:19:09.211 --> 01:19:11.747
HE CAN GO ON
HAVING BIRTHDAYS,
AND YOU CAN STOP.

01:19:13.181 --> 01:19:16.284
I SAW A GRAY HAIR
THE OTHER DAY, HARRY.

01:19:16.284 --> 01:19:18.787
LISTEN...

01:19:18.787 --> 01:19:23.125
YOU AND ERNIE WILL
ACTUALLY BE AGING
TOWARD EACH OTHER.

01:19:23.125 --> 01:19:25.827
OLDER PEOPLE START
GOING BACKWARDS
AT SOME POINT,

01:19:25.827 --> 01:19:29.564
AND, UH, WELL,
EVENTUALLY YOU'LL
MEET IN THE MIDDLE.

01:19:34.669 --> 01:19:37.105
AM I MAKING
A MISTAKE, HARRY?

01:19:38.807 --> 01:19:41.376
IT'S NOT JUST
THE AGE DIFFERENCE. IT'S--

01:19:41.376 --> 01:19:43.044
YOU LOVE HIM.

01:19:43.044 --> 01:19:44.646
THAT'S WHAT COUNTS.

01:19:46.515 --> 01:19:50.786
LISTEN TO YOU...
THE VOICE OF EXPERIENCE.

01:20:20.916 --> 01:20:22.017
AGGIE?

01:20:22.017 --> 01:20:23.084
HMM?

01:20:23.084 --> 01:20:24.886
I HAVE TO ASK YOU
A QUESTION.

01:20:24.886 --> 01:20:25.887
HMM, CAN'T IT WAIT

01:20:25.887 --> 01:20:27.722
TILL I'VE HAD
A FEW HOURS OF SLEEP?

01:20:27.722 --> 01:20:29.424
NO. THIS IS IMPORTANT.

01:20:29.424 --> 01:20:30.492
HMM.

01:20:30.492 --> 01:20:33.128
JUST PROMISE ME
YOU WON'T SAY NO.

01:20:33.128 --> 01:20:34.362
NO TO WHAT?

01:20:34.362 --> 01:20:38.700
JUST PROMISE.
THIS IS VERY, VERY
IMPORTANT TO ME.

01:20:38.700 --> 01:20:40.702
OK, I PROMISE.

01:20:40.702 --> 01:20:43.104
NOW CAN I HAVE
A FEW HOURS OF SLEEP?

01:20:43.104 --> 01:20:44.539
FINE.

01:20:47.042 --> 01:20:50.412
WE'RE GOING TO SPEND
THE WEEKEND WITH
THE GOOD DOCTOR.

01:20:53.648 --> 01:20:55.250
DOCTOR CARACCIOLO?

01:20:59.054 --> 01:21:00.388
I--I DON'T THINK THAT--

01:21:00.388 --> 01:21:02.390
AT HIS MOTHER'S HOUSE.

01:21:02.390 --> 01:21:03.959
YOU JUST SWORE TO ME.

01:21:03.959 --> 01:21:06.561
YOU JUST GAVE ME
YOUR SOLEMN WORD.

01:21:08.463 --> 01:21:10.232
I DON'T HAVE
ANYTHING TO WEAR.

01:21:10.232 --> 01:21:12.634
AGGIE, HE'S A DOCTOR.

01:21:12.634 --> 01:21:14.369
HOW FANCY CAN IT BE?

01:21:32.554 --> 01:21:34.022
CUSATEMI,
MA FACCIO STRADA.

01:21:34.022 --> 01:21:35.290
OH.

01:21:47.435 --> 01:21:49.271
[BELL RINGS]

01:22:03.652 --> 01:22:05.353
COME, COME.

01:22:34.449 --> 01:22:35.850
OH!

01:22:39.587 --> 01:22:41.756
Agnes:
YOU NEVER TOLD US
ABOUT ANY OF THIS.

01:22:41.756 --> 01:22:45.193
Caracciolo:
I WAS AFRAID
YOU MIGHT NOT COME.

01:22:45.193 --> 01:22:48.396
IT'S SO VERY BEAUTIFUL.

01:22:48.396 --> 01:22:51.333
IT IS YOU
THAT ARE BEAUTIFUL.

01:22:56.438 --> 01:22:58.506
[CHURCH BELLS PEAL]

01:23:11.987 --> 01:23:16.224
[SPEAKING ITALIAN]

01:23:18.593 --> 01:23:20.996
ARE--ARE THESE BASS?

01:23:20.996 --> 01:23:22.564
BA-BASS?

01:23:22.564 --> 01:23:24.699
AH, NON CAPISCO.

01:23:24.699 --> 01:23:26.901
ALL RIGHT.

01:23:30.605 --> 01:23:32.807
IT IS THE BEST MOMENT,
EARLY IN THE MORNING.

01:23:32.807 --> 01:23:35.977
YES.

01:23:35.977 --> 01:23:40.382
I DO NOT WISH TO HURT
MAC'S FEELINGS, BUT...

01:23:40.382 --> 01:23:44.652
IT WOULD PLEASE ME
SO GREATLY IF YOU...

01:23:44.652 --> 01:23:46.187
JUST YOU ALONE...

01:23:46.187 --> 01:23:49.824
WOULD COME
BACK TO VENICE
ON YOUR NEXT BREAK.

01:23:55.130 --> 01:23:57.065
D-DOMENICO, I--

01:23:57.065 --> 01:23:59.434
HELLO.

01:23:59.434 --> 01:24:01.970
COME ON, LOOK AT THESE.
THEY'RE GREAT.

01:24:01.970 --> 01:24:04.339
AH, HOW ABOUT ME
AS A CLOWN?

01:24:04.339 --> 01:24:05.673
OH, WHY WOULD
THAT BE DIFFERENT?

01:24:05.673 --> 01:24:08.309
YEAH, I'M GOING TO TAKE
ONE OF THESE HOME. UM...

01:24:14.215 --> 01:24:16.951
Domenico:
I WOULD BUY ANY MASK
FOR YOU.

01:24:20.555 --> 01:24:23.691
BUT THIS IS THE ONE
I WOULD CHOOSE.

01:24:23.691 --> 01:24:25.293
JUST HOLD IT RIGHT
THERE, MR. HEMINGWAY.

01:24:25.293 --> 01:24:27.128
JUST A COUPLE
OF MORE QUESTIONS,
MR. HEMINGWAY.

01:24:27.128 --> 01:24:29.330
HOW'D YOU FEEL ABOUT
BEING THE FIRST AMERICAN--

01:24:29.330 --> 01:24:30.532
THANK YOU, MA'AM--

01:24:30.532 --> 01:24:34.335
ABOUT BEING
THE FIRST AMERICAN
WOUNDED IN ITALY?

01:24:34.335 --> 01:24:36.171
WELL, I WOULD HAVE
MUCH RATHER BEEN
THE LAST.

01:24:36.171 --> 01:24:37.305
[LAUGHING]

01:24:37.305 --> 01:24:39.007
YOU MUST BE VERY PROUD
OF HIM, MRS. HEMINGWAY.

01:24:39.007 --> 01:24:42.444
ERNEST WAS A HERO
TO THIS FAMILY LONG
BEFORE HE WENT TO WAR.

01:24:42.444 --> 01:24:44.679
HOW EXACTLY
WERE YOU WOUNDED?

01:24:44.679 --> 01:24:47.715
LIKE I SAID, I WAS
JUST FOOLING AROUND
IN THE TRENCHES.

01:24:47.715 --> 01:24:49.951
I'M SORRY, FOLKS,
THAT'S ENOUGH.

01:24:49.951 --> 01:24:51.886
I HAVE PATIENTS
SCHEDULED.

01:24:51.886 --> 01:24:53.455
JUST ONE MORE QUESTION,
DR. HEMINGWAY.

01:24:53.455 --> 01:24:56.057
DID YOU FALL FOR ANY
OF THOSE ITALIAN BEAUTIES,
ERNIE?

01:24:56.057 --> 01:24:58.460
NO, BUT I MET JUST
ABOUT THE BEST-LOOKING
AMERICAN GIRL

01:24:58.460 --> 01:25:00.161
YOU EVER SAW OVER THERE.

01:25:00.161 --> 01:25:02.297
CAN WE HAVE HER NAME?

01:25:02.297 --> 01:25:05.266
MRS. HEMINGWAY,
SOON AS THE WAR ENDS.

01:25:05.266 --> 01:25:06.334
[CHUCKLES]

01:25:08.069 --> 01:25:10.004
Woman: ANOTHER ONE
FOR YOU, CHARLOTTE.

01:25:12.740 --> 01:25:14.509
Ernest: SO I TOLD THE FOLKS
ALL ABOUT US.

01:25:14.509 --> 01:25:19.681
JUST KNOW YOU'LL
WIN THEM ROUND,
THE MOMENT YOU ARRIVE.

01:25:19.681 --> 01:25:21.149
ONCE WE'RE MARRIED,

01:25:21.149 --> 01:25:25.453
I'M SURE POPS WILL
LET US LIVE IN HIS CABIN
ON WALLOON LAKE.

01:25:25.453 --> 01:25:29.858
IMAGINE. YOU'LL BE
MAKING THE OLD PLACE
SPICK-AND-SPAN,

01:25:29.858 --> 01:25:32.360
WHILE I WRITE GREAT WORKS.

01:25:32.360 --> 01:25:33.962
I HAVEN'T HEARD
FROM YOU IN OVER A WEEK,

01:25:33.962 --> 01:25:37.632
SO I JUST HOPE THAT
YOU'RE SAFE AND WELL.

01:25:47.008 --> 01:25:50.044
HEY, ERNIE! ERNIE!

01:25:50.044 --> 01:25:51.546
WAIT, LET'S SEE THEM
AGAIN, ERNIE.

01:25:51.546 --> 01:25:53.915
ERNIE, WAIT!

01:25:55.049 --> 01:25:56.284
[CAR HORN BLARES]

01:25:56.284 --> 01:25:58.119
[DOG BARKING]

01:25:58.119 --> 01:25:59.787
WAIT!

01:26:01.022 --> 01:26:02.023
LET'S SEE THEM AGAIN,
ERNIE.

01:26:02.023 --> 01:26:03.024
HI, JOE.

01:26:03.024 --> 01:26:04.359
HOW MANY OF THEM
WENT IN YOU?

01:26:04.359 --> 01:26:05.493
227.

01:26:05.493 --> 01:26:08.363
JUST LIKE THESE.

01:26:08.363 --> 01:26:11.232
NOTHING FROM ITALY.
SORRY, ERNIE.

01:26:11.232 --> 01:26:12.700
I CAN'T COMPLAIN.

01:26:12.700 --> 01:26:16.304
SHE SENDS ME
A TELEGRAM PRACTICALLY
EVERY OTHER DAY.

01:26:18.173 --> 01:26:20.008
FIRST ALL I KNEW
WAS BUON GIORNO,

01:26:20.008 --> 01:26:24.279
BUT NOW, YOUR POOR BROTHER
HAS TO SIT THROUGH
MY CONJUGATION OF VERBS.

01:26:24.279 --> 01:26:26.614
AGNES SEEMS TO LIVE
ONLY IN THE PRESENT.

01:26:26.614 --> 01:26:31.186
SHE HAS TROUBLE
WITH THE PAST TENSE,
PERFETTO E IMPERFETTO.

01:26:31.186 --> 01:26:32.253
FIRMATO,
SIGNOR CONTE.

01:26:32.253 --> 01:26:34.989
I LIKE TO CONCENTRATE
ON THE HERE AND NOW.

01:26:34.989 --> 01:26:36.057
AMICI MIEI.

01:26:36.057 --> 01:26:39.561
MY DEARS, I HAVE
WONDERFUL NEWS.

01:26:39.561 --> 01:26:41.696
THE ARMISTICE
HAS BEEN SIGNED.

01:26:41.696 --> 01:26:43.798
[BELLS PEALING OUTSIDE]

01:26:43.798 --> 01:26:45.533
THE WAR IS OVER.

01:27:00.748 --> 01:27:04.285
NOW I SUPPOSE THAT
THE RED CROSS WILL POST
YOU BACK TO AMERICA.

01:27:04.285 --> 01:27:05.286
HMM.

01:27:05.286 --> 01:27:07.355
IS THAT TO BE
YOUR FUTURE?

01:27:07.355 --> 01:27:12.760
OH, I DON'T KNOW,
DOMENICO.

01:27:12.760 --> 01:27:14.896
MAY HAVE
TO GIVE IT UP.

01:27:14.896 --> 01:27:18.533
BUT WHY? MEDICINE
IS YOUR LIFE
AS IT IS MINE.

01:27:18.533 --> 01:27:20.101
HMM.

01:27:21.569 --> 01:27:22.904
MAY I SAY SOMETHING?

01:27:22.904 --> 01:27:23.905
OF COURSE.

01:27:23.905 --> 01:27:24.906
I--

01:27:24.906 --> 01:27:25.974
LOOK.

01:27:26.908 --> 01:27:28.476
OH.

01:27:29.510 --> 01:27:31.479
[DOMENICO LAUGHING]

01:27:33.781 --> 01:27:38.086
I WAS GOING TO SAY
I'VE NEVER WORKED

01:27:38.086 --> 01:27:41.322
WITH A MORE
GIFTED NURSE.

01:27:41.322 --> 01:27:43.625
I WOULD HATE
TO GIVE IT UP.

01:27:47.528 --> 01:27:50.898
HEY! E' FINITA!

01:27:51.833 --> 01:27:55.169
OVER THERE WILL BE
THE MATERNITY WARD,

01:27:55.169 --> 01:27:56.804
AND THERE
THE OPERATING ROOM.

01:27:56.804 --> 01:27:57.905
WONDERFUL.

01:27:57.905 --> 01:28:00.074
WHERE I WILL BE ABLE
TO DO THE, UM...

01:28:00.074 --> 01:28:04.746
TAGLIO CESAREO
AND OTHER SURGERY
WHEN NEEDED.

01:28:04.746 --> 01:28:06.648
IT'S EXCITING.

01:28:06.648 --> 01:28:09.817
OF COURSE, IT WILL
BE NOT SO IMPRESSIVE

01:28:09.817 --> 01:28:10.985
LIKE YOUR
SAINT JOHN HOPKINS,

01:28:10.985 --> 01:28:15.456
BUT IT WILL BE DONE
WITH LOVE.

01:28:21.562 --> 01:28:24.732
WHY IS IT,
SIGNORINA AGNES,

01:28:24.732 --> 01:28:27.101
I CAN PERFORM
6 HOURS OF SURGERY

01:28:27.101 --> 01:28:29.537
WITHOUT
THE SLIGHTEST FEAR,
AND NOW...

01:28:32.473 --> 01:28:35.243
AND NOW MI STO
MORENDO DI PAURA.

01:28:35.243 --> 01:28:37.178
EXCUSE ME.

01:28:39.347 --> 01:28:40.782
WE SHOULD BE GOING NOW.

01:28:42.283 --> 01:28:44.619
I'M SORRY
I BROUGHT YOU HERE.

01:28:48.790 --> 01:28:50.758
NO, NO. WAIT.

01:28:52.794 --> 01:28:55.263
IN FONDO COSA
CHE IO VOGLIO
DOMANDARVI á SE...

01:28:55.263 --> 01:28:57.265
[SIGHS]

01:28:57.265 --> 01:29:00.335
I'M SORRY.

01:29:00.335 --> 01:29:04.272
WHAT I'M ASKING, AGNES,
IS...

01:29:04.272 --> 01:29:07.842
WILL DO YOU ME THE HONOR
TO BE MY WIFE?

01:29:13.414 --> 01:29:15.183
PRESTO, PRESTO!

01:29:16.884 --> 01:29:18.486
PRESTO!

01:29:21.889 --> 01:29:23.791
I'M SURE MISS VON KUROWSKY
HAS TOLD YOU

01:29:23.791 --> 01:29:26.761
WE WILL MISS YOU ALL
VERY MUCH.

01:29:26.761 --> 01:29:29.397
YOU'VE DONE
A WONDERFUL JOB.
BRAVO.

01:29:30.832 --> 01:29:32.233
AGNES!

01:29:32.233 --> 01:29:35.703
THE PORTERS NEED
TO KNOW WHICH TRANSPORT
YOUR BAGS GO ON.

01:29:38.740 --> 01:29:40.341
YOU HAVE TO MAKE UP
YOUR MIND.

01:29:43.077 --> 01:29:44.712
GOING TO VENICE.

01:29:44.712 --> 01:29:47.048
De Long: COME ALONG,
EVERYONE THAT'S GOING.
LET'S GO.

01:29:47.048 --> 01:29:49.784
NO...

01:29:49.784 --> 01:29:51.753
NO, I DON'T KNOW.
I--I--I DON'T--

01:29:51.753 --> 01:29:54.689
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO.

01:29:54.689 --> 01:29:56.691
[SIGHS]

01:29:56.691 --> 01:29:58.993
I CAN'T STOP
THINKING ABOUT HIM.

01:29:58.993 --> 01:30:00.395
THE KID?

01:30:04.932 --> 01:30:05.933
AGNES...

01:30:05.933 --> 01:30:07.135
MMM.

01:30:07.135 --> 01:30:08.136
COME ON.

01:30:08.136 --> 01:30:11.606
JUST SEE IT
FOR WHAT IT WAS.

01:30:11.606 --> 01:30:12.607
A FLIRTATION.

01:30:12.607 --> 01:30:14.175
[CHUCKLES]

01:30:14.175 --> 01:30:18.379
MAYBE EVEN A FLING,
BUT THAT IS ALL
THAT IT WAS.

01:30:18.379 --> 01:30:22.083
OH, MAC, IT WAS...
IT WAS MORE THAN
JUST A FLING.

01:30:22.083 --> 01:30:25.119
I TOLD HIM
I WOULD MARRY HIM.

01:30:26.421 --> 01:30:28.489
YOU CAN'T MARRY
ERNEST HEMINGWAY.

01:30:28.489 --> 01:30:31.125
I MEAN...HE'S A CHILD.

01:30:33.694 --> 01:30:36.264
YOU NEVER LIKED HIM
MUCH, DID YOU?

01:30:36.264 --> 01:30:37.698
NO.

01:30:37.698 --> 01:30:39.367
OH...

01:30:39.367 --> 01:30:41.502
NO. I LIKED HIM FINE,

01:30:41.502 --> 01:30:43.504
AND I THINK HE'S
AS GOOD-LOOKING AS SIN,

01:30:43.504 --> 01:30:48.776
BUT, MY GOD, AGGIE...
HE IS NOT A HUSBAND.

01:30:51.712 --> 01:30:54.749
BUT WHATEVER YOU DECIDE...

01:30:54.749 --> 01:30:56.851
I'M WITH YOU ALL THE WAY.

01:30:58.085 --> 01:30:59.720
OH, MAC.

01:30:59.720 --> 01:31:03.057
I CAN'T BEAR
THE THOUGHT
OF YOU LEAVING.

01:31:06.661 --> 01:31:09.397
AND ONCE AGAIN,
YOU ARE RIGHT.

01:31:09.397 --> 01:31:12.366
I MUST START THINKING
WITH MY HEAD.

01:31:24.946 --> 01:31:26.848
Agnes: DEAR KID...

01:31:26.848 --> 01:31:30.218
THIS IS THE MOST
DIFFICULT LETTER
I'VE EVER HAD TO WRITE.

01:31:30.218 --> 01:31:34.922
AND I'M AFRAID IT'S GOING
TO HURT YOU A GREAT DEAL.

01:31:34.922 --> 01:31:37.692
BUT DR. CARACCIOLO
HAS OFFERED ME
A WONDERFUL OPPORTUNITY

01:31:37.692 --> 01:31:41.062
TO HELP HIM SET UP
A NEW HOSPITAL HERE.

01:31:41.062 --> 01:31:42.763
AND HE'S ALSO ASKED ME
TO MARRY HIM,

01:31:42.763 --> 01:31:46.501
AND I HAVE AGREED
TO CONSIDER THIS.

01:31:46.501 --> 01:31:48.102
WHAT I DO HAVE
TO RECOGNIZE, THOUGH,

01:31:48.102 --> 01:31:50.004
IS THAT YOU AND I
ARE YEARS APART,

01:31:50.004 --> 01:31:52.607
AND IT WOULD BE
SO VERY WRONG OF ME
TO TIE YOU DOWN

01:31:52.607 --> 01:31:57.778
WHEN THERE ARE SO MANY
STORIES YET TO WRITE.

01:31:57.778 --> 01:32:00.815
SO AFTER A LONG THINK
BY MYSELF,

01:32:00.815 --> 01:32:04.719
I HAVE DECIDED
THAT OUR RELATIONSHIP
MUST COME TO AN END.

01:32:41.789 --> 01:32:43.958
Mrs. Hemingway: ERNIE!

01:32:43.958 --> 01:32:45.693
ERNIE, WHAT'S HAPPENED?

01:32:45.693 --> 01:32:47.862
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]
ERNIE!

01:32:47.862 --> 01:32:50.932
ERNIE, OPEN THIS DOOR,
DO YOU HEAR?

01:32:50.932 --> 01:32:53.034
I'M GOING TO GET
YOUR FATHER!

01:33:15.256 --> 01:33:17.291
[CRYING]

01:33:38.212 --> 01:33:44.385
AGNES, MY BROTHER
HAS WAITED A LONG TIME
TO FIND TRUE LOVE.

01:33:44.385 --> 01:33:47.722
I DO HOPE
YOU WILL SAY YES.

01:33:47.722 --> 01:33:50.424
YOU COULD BE
SO HAPPY HERE.

01:33:52.159 --> 01:33:53.728
MAY I?

01:33:57.031 --> 01:33:58.899
I LOVE TO DANCE.

01:34:02.203 --> 01:34:04.271
[WALTZ PLAYING]

01:34:25.326 --> 01:34:27.528
DOLCE AGNES...

01:34:27.528 --> 01:34:29.530
HAVING YOU IN MY ARMS

01:34:29.530 --> 01:34:32.633
MAKE THIS THE MOST BEAUTIFUL
WALTZ IN THE WORLD.

01:35:22.783 --> 01:35:23.851
[CAR HORN HONKS]

01:35:29.824 --> 01:35:32.793
Man: TAXI. TAXI.

01:35:32.793 --> 01:35:33.861
GOOD DAY, MA'AM.

01:35:48.442 --> 01:35:51.512
I BELIEVE THERE'S
A RESERVATION FOR...
EXCUSE ME.

01:35:52.680 --> 01:35:55.616
AGNES, HOW GREAT
TO SEE YOU.

01:35:55.616 --> 01:35:58.219
YOU TOO, HARRY.

01:35:58.219 --> 01:35:59.220
WON'T YOU...

01:35:59.220 --> 01:36:01.589
THANK YOU.
YOU LOOK SO GROWN UP.

01:36:04.024 --> 01:36:05.593
I MUST SAY, A SUIT
LOOKS MUCH BETTER ON YOU

01:36:05.593 --> 01:36:06.727
THAN A PAIR OF PAJAMAS.

01:36:06.727 --> 01:36:09.697
YOU LOOK
JUST AS BEAUTIFUL.

01:36:11.165 --> 01:36:14.969
I, UH, I TOOK THE LIBERTY
OF ORDERING A CHIANTI

01:36:14.969 --> 01:36:16.437
FOR OLD TIMES' SAKE.

01:36:16.437 --> 01:36:18.506
UH, MAY I?

01:36:27.314 --> 01:36:29.383
FOR OLD TIMES' SAKE.

01:36:35.556 --> 01:36:38.659
FEELS MORE LIKE
A HUNDRED YEARS THAN...

01:36:38.659 --> 01:36:41.996
8 MONTHS, IS IT, SINCE
WE SAW EACH OTHER LAST?

01:36:41.996 --> 01:36:43.597
DO YOU REMEMBER?

01:36:43.597 --> 01:36:45.533
CERTAINLY. YOU WERE...

01:36:45.533 --> 01:36:49.170
GIVING FRONT-LINE ADVICE
TO THE LOVELORN.

01:36:49.170 --> 01:36:53.340
WHICH I, UH, UNDERSTOOD
YOU DIDN'T TAKE.

01:36:54.542 --> 01:36:58.746
I'D, UH...I'D HEARD YOU'D
MARRIED THE GOOD DOCTOR,

01:36:58.746 --> 01:37:01.682
BUT I--I DON'T SEE
A WEDDING RING.

01:37:01.682 --> 01:37:05.553
NO, NO, I DIDN'T
MARRY DOMENICO.

01:37:05.553 --> 01:37:10.090
I THINK I'VE MADE
A MESS OF THINGS ALL
THE WAY AROUND, HARRY.

01:37:13.594 --> 01:37:15.663
HOW DID YOU HEAR
I WAS MARRIED?

01:37:15.663 --> 01:37:18.232
HOW DO YOU THINK?

01:37:18.232 --> 01:37:22.069
I HEARD THROUGH AN ANGRY,
GIN-SOAKED VOICE

01:37:22.069 --> 01:37:24.538
OVER THE TELEPHONE
AT 3:00 IN THE MORNING.

01:37:27.208 --> 01:37:30.778
DO YOU EVER SEE HIM?

01:37:30.778 --> 01:37:32.813
NO.

01:37:32.813 --> 01:37:37.451
BUT I GET RAGING,
RAMBLING LETTERS FROM HIM,

01:37:37.451 --> 01:37:40.554
MOSTLY ABOUT YOU.

01:37:40.554 --> 01:37:42.756
HE'S VERY ANGRY.

01:37:42.756 --> 01:37:46.961
HE HAS EVERY RIGHT
TO BE.

01:37:51.832 --> 01:37:54.101
WHERE IS HE?

01:37:54.101 --> 01:37:57.705
WELL, HE'S AT WALLOON LAKE.

01:37:57.705 --> 01:37:59.206
TRYING HIS HAND
AT SCRIBBLING.

01:37:59.206 --> 01:38:01.842
LIVING OFF HIS OLD MAN,
IF YOU ASK ME.

01:38:06.480 --> 01:38:09.116
DO YOU MIND
IF I ASK YOU SOMETHING?

01:38:09.116 --> 01:38:10.751
HMM.

01:38:14.221 --> 01:38:16.290
DO YOU LOVE HIM?

01:38:27.067 --> 01:38:28.836
DID YOU EVER TELL HIM?

01:38:36.844 --> 01:38:38.913
YES.

01:38:42.182 --> 01:38:44.618
BUT I DON'T THINK
HE HEARD.

01:38:52.026 --> 01:38:57.097
DON'T YOU THINK
IT MIGHT BE A GOOD IDEA
TO TELL HIM NOW?

01:40:17.378 --> 01:40:19.847
CATCH ANY BASS?

01:40:34.828 --> 01:40:36.697
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

01:40:36.697 --> 01:40:38.832
THERE ARE SOME THINGS
THAT NEEDED TO BE SAID.

01:40:38.832 --> 01:40:43.337
I JUST HOPE
IT'S NOT TOO LATE.

01:41:12.900 --> 01:41:14.968
DO YOU WANT A DRINK?

01:41:16.937 --> 01:41:19.640
[AHEM]
ALL RIGHT.

01:41:19.640 --> 01:41:22.910
IN THAT CASE,
I'LL HAVE ONE, TOO.

01:41:26.847 --> 01:41:28.949
HOW'S YOUR LEG?

01:41:31.718 --> 01:41:35.456
IS THAT A PERSONAL OR
A PROFESSIONAL QUESTION?

01:41:42.429 --> 01:41:43.797
ERNIE--

01:41:43.797 --> 01:41:45.799
ABSENT FRIENDS.

01:42:14.795 --> 01:42:17.531
DO YOU REMEMBER DOTTIE?

01:42:17.531 --> 01:42:22.069
SHE...SHE MARRIED
BURNSIDE...

01:42:22.069 --> 01:42:26.306
OF ALL PEOPLE.

01:42:26.306 --> 01:42:28.275
AND ROSIE?

01:42:28.275 --> 01:42:30.043
ROSIE RAN OFF
WITH LARKIN.

01:42:30.043 --> 01:42:36.717
MAC SAID
IF I SEE YOU AGAIN,
I SHOULD SAY HELLO.

01:42:36.717 --> 01:42:39.520
AS YOU'D EXPECT,
SHE'S STILL
WITH THE RED CROSS.

01:42:39.520 --> 01:42:44.158
IT'S, UH...

01:42:44.158 --> 01:42:46.727
SHE'S NURSING IN CUBA.

01:42:50.697 --> 01:42:56.003
BIRDSEED. NEVER LIKED HIM.

01:42:56.003 --> 01:42:59.306
POMPOUS ASS.

01:42:59.306 --> 01:43:01.875
ARE YOU IN TOUCH
WITH ANY OF THE BOYS?

01:43:03.443 --> 01:43:05.712
HARRY SOMETIMES.

01:43:05.712 --> 01:43:09.816
YES, HE SAYS YOU'VE
BEEN...WRITING.

01:43:12.252 --> 01:43:13.687
SOLD A FEW PIECES.

01:43:21.261 --> 01:43:23.864
JESUS, IT'S STUFFY
IN HERE.

01:43:51.792 --> 01:43:54.828
BEAUTIFUL.

01:43:54.828 --> 01:43:57.898
JUST AS I'D IMAGINED
IT WOULD BE.

01:43:59.800 --> 01:44:02.669
MY LITTLE PALAZZO
IN THE WOODS.

01:44:08.942 --> 01:44:12.579
I HEARD YOU AND, UH,
DR. WHAT'S-HIS-NAME
DIDN'T GO THROUGH WITH IT.

01:44:14.915 --> 01:44:16.516
WHY NOT?

01:44:16.516 --> 01:44:18.385
TOO OLD?

01:44:19.987 --> 01:44:22.689
IT WAS A MISTAKE.

01:44:25.125 --> 01:44:28.629
THERE WAS ALWAYS
SOMEBODY ELSE.

01:44:29.696 --> 01:44:32.199
ANYONE I KNOW?

01:44:34.234 --> 01:44:36.937
WHO ELSE BUT YOU, ERNIE?

01:44:39.273 --> 01:44:41.842
IT STILL IS. THAT'S WHY
I HAD TO COME BACK HERE,

01:44:41.842 --> 01:44:43.343
AND I HAD TO TELL YOU
HOW SORRY I AM.

01:44:43.343 --> 01:44:45.078
SORRY FOR WHAT?

01:44:45.078 --> 01:44:46.913
IT WAS THE WAR.

01:44:46.913 --> 01:44:49.549
LOT OF THINGS HAPPEN
IN THE WAR.

01:44:51.151 --> 01:44:52.953
WHAT DID EITHER
OF US KNOW?

01:44:52.953 --> 01:44:54.288
NO, WE KNEW.

01:44:54.288 --> 01:44:57.557
WE KNEW.
YOU CAN'T DENY THAT.

01:44:57.557 --> 01:45:00.861
WE HAD A FLING...
KID STUFF.

01:45:21.114 --> 01:45:24.017
THERE'S STILL
A PART OF ME THAT...

01:45:24.017 --> 01:45:28.655
WANTS TO TAKE YOU
IN MY ARMS.

01:45:28.655 --> 01:45:31.525
JUST LIKE IT USED TO BE.

01:45:33.827 --> 01:45:35.996
BUT I'VE CHANGED.

01:45:35.996 --> 01:45:37.964
OF COURSE.
THINGS CHANGE.

01:45:39.900 --> 01:45:42.803
IT WOULDN'T WORK.

01:45:45.605 --> 01:45:47.307
NOT NOW.

01:45:48.842 --> 01:45:52.279
NOT THIS TIME.

01:46:00.220 --> 01:46:03.357
OH, KID.

01:46:04.791 --> 01:46:08.929
KID GREW UP, AG.

01:46:10.063 --> 01:46:11.732
THANKS TO YOU.

01:46:47.501 --> 01:46:49.102
I LOVE YOU.

01:47:17.764 --> 01:47:22.202
I'LL LOVE YOU
AS LONG AS I LIVE.

01:47:57.037 --> 01:48:02.342
Agnes: I NEVER SAW ERNIE AGAIN
AFTER WALLOON LAKE.

01:48:02.342 --> 01:48:06.179
I OFTEN WONDER
WHAT MIGHT HAVE HAPPENED

01:48:06.179 --> 01:48:09.249
IF HE HAD TAKEN ME
IN HIS ARMS.

01:48:09.249 --> 01:48:14.788
BUT I GUESS HIS PRIDE
MEANT HE WASN'T ABLE
TO FORGIVE ME.

01:48:14.788 --> 01:48:20.126
SOME SAY HE LIVED
WITH THE PAIN OF IT
ALL HIS LIFE.

01:48:20.126 --> 01:48:23.396
THE HURT BOY BECAME
THE ANGRY MAN,

01:48:23.396 --> 01:48:28.101
A BRILLIANT,
TOUGH ADVENTURER,

01:48:28.101 --> 01:48:32.806
WHO WAS THE MOST FAMOUS
WRITER OF HIS GENERATION.

01:48:32.806 --> 01:48:35.909
AND THE KID HE HAD BEEN...

01:48:35.909 --> 01:48:44.584
EAGER...IDEALISTIC...
AND TENDER...

01:48:44.584 --> 01:48:46.553
LIVED ON ONLY IN MY HEART.

